(211, 42, 'The Floral Clock', 'Between the Botanical Gardens and Queenston Heights Park stands one of the most popular sights to view in Niagara. The Floral Clock is a 12.2-m (40-ft.) diameter working clock that is one of the largest in the world.  Once you have taken all you photos with the colourful clock you can take time to go souvenir shopping. ', 'Queenston Heights Park, Niagara Parkway, Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada', '2:30 pm', '43.159306', '-79.05541099999999', 1, '2018-09-03 15:03:19'),
(212, 42, 'Queenston Heights Stopover ', 'Stopover at Queenston Heights, which borders Canada and the United States with only the Niagara River separating them. Are you a history buff? Come with us and learn about the famous Battle of Queenston Heights. Queenston Heights Park is the site of a War of 1812 battle in which Sir Isaac Brock was killed. A 50-m. (150-ft.) monument, that is perched above the Niagara Escarpment, was built in his honour.  4:15 pm: Stopover in Niagara-on-the-lake for 60-75 MINUTES. You will appreciate the quaint shops and boutiques that line Queen Street, the main drag of Niagara-on-the-Lake, as well as the proximity of wineries, brew pubs and even a chocolate factory! ', 'Queenston Heights Park, Niagara Parkway, Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada', '3:00 pm', '43.159306', '-79.05541099999999', 1, '2018-09-03 15:03:19'),
(213, 42, 'Winery Tour ', 'Complimentary wine and grape juice tasting is available.  Be treated as a wine connoisseur at a world-class winery. Buy local-made wines of your choice. World famous Canadian  Ice Wines are available here. ', 'Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada', '5:00 pm', '43.2549988', '-79.07726159999999', 1, '2018-09-03 15:03:19'),
(214, 42, ' Back to Downtown Toronto and Airport Hotels', 'The tour ends back where it started, your camera will be full of memories that will last forever!', 'Toronto, ON, Canada', '7:00- 7.30 pm', '43.653226', '-79.38318429999998', 1, '2018-09-03 15:03:19');
INSERT INTO `tour_reviews` (`ID`, `tour_id`, `name`, `email`, `website`, `description`, `count_star`, `author_IP`, `created_on`, `status`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1, 4, 'e Thompson', 'ethompson@htmail.com', '', 'Great day at Niagara Falls and Niagara on the Lake ! Excellent tour of Niagara Falls area, well organised by Alisha and driver Eli. Both were very friendly, helpful and entertaining! Hornblower boat took us right into the centre of Horseshoe Falls, which was a fantastic experience - unforgettable ! Niagara on the Lake is a very pretty area, with beautiful houses, interesting variety of shops, and lovely plants &amp; flowers adding to its appeal. Day out ran pretty well to schedule, thanks to Alisha &amp; Eli.\r\nI would recommend ToNiagara tour company for a great day out to Niagara Falls and area.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-09-03 02:02:17', 0, '2018-09-03 02:02:17'),
(2, 4, 'Aixa L', 'aixal@htmail.com', '', 'This tour is amazing...the tour guides were awesome!!! It was worth the money. I definitely recommend  this tour:))', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-09-03 02:00:49', 0, '2018-09-03 02:00:49'),
(3, 4, 'Nohely M', 'nohelym@htmail.com', '', 'Awesome experience overall.  My first tour ever &amp; it was just amazing as well as the tour guides and drivers Thank you so much!', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-27 14:21:45', 1, '2018-08-27 14:21:45'),
(4, 9, 'S Harris', 'sharris@htmail.com', '', 'We live in Niagara Falls and each time we have company, the first choice for an attraction is Hornblower. Recently we had 3 first time visitors to Canada who cannot stop talking about the experience. Thank you for the joy brought to us and our visitors each and every time!!!!', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-25 13:32:49', 1, '2018-08-25 13:32:49'),
(5, 15, 'Vishal P', 'vishalp@htmail.com', '', 'This is the first time we visited toronto and we wanted a private tour of niagara falls. This is great for those who have a short trip and only want to see certain places. The tour guide was friendly and very knowledgeable.  We got picked up in a nice air conditioned GMC and it had plenty of space.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-23 14:40:24', 1, '2018-08-23 14:40:24'),
(6, 4, 'Raina S', 'rainas@htmail.com', '', 'Had an awesome day with ToNiagara! Our tour guide (Alisha) was great, very helpful and very knowledgeable. Best part of the day was being able to skip the line to get on the Hornblower boat!! Incredible experience, and super seamless support.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-23 00:46:41', 1, '2018-08-23 00:46:41'),
(7, 4, 'E Kelly', 'ekelly@htmail.com', '', 'Our whole tri to Niagara Falls was excellent value. We had a great time taking in all the experiences of the Falls. I especially want to thank Eddy from Sydney Nova Scotia for getting us to the Greyhound terminal on time.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-23 00:44:45', 1, '2018-08-23 00:44:45'),
(8, 4, 'L Doyle', 'ldoyle@htmail.com', '', 'Great experience from start to finish . Our bus driver Huron (apologies if the spelling is incorrect) and tour guide Joe were very knowledgeable and entertaining. The boat trip itself was amazing plus we had the extra bonus of having lunch with a view in the Sheraton hotel from the 13th floor . Our extra stops at the smallest chapel, the very quaint and beautiful Niagara on the lake and the winery were also great . This is a must do trip if you are in Toronto. It represents great value and I highly recommend it . Thanks for a great day!!!!', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-14 13:42:48', 1, '2018-08-14 13:42:48'),
(9, 4, 'B Shervington', 'BShervington@htmail.com', '', 'We had a wonderful time at Niagara Falls. The boat trip on Hornblower was great and it was so exciting to get close to the falls. I would highly recommend the trip and hopefully can do it again.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-14 13:38:15', 1, '2018-08-14 13:38:15'),
(10, 5, 'I Geografija', 'lgeografija@hotmail.com', '', 'Excellent tour. All in time and much more.', 5, '70.54.46.67', '2018-08-14 13:34:53', 1, '2018-08-14 13:34:53'),
(11, 4, 'Charlotte T', 'charlotte@htmail.com', '', 'Such a fabulous day. SO much packed in. Great value! Really helpful tour guide, although the sound system on the bus wasn\\\'t great he didn\\\'t mind us asking him questions to clarify! Strongly recommend - and the queue jump for the Hornblower means you get so much more time to see the surrounding area. An experience of a lifetime!', 5, '76.67.135.44', '2018-08-04 15:35:11', 1, '2018-08-04 15:35:11'),
(12, 4, 'Gaurie N', 'gourien@htmail.com', '', 'I booked a tour for 3 guests to Niagara. Nick was most helpful in assisting me with the details. My guests were picked up from their hotel promptly. They  loved the tour and the friendly tour guide.  It was the highlight of their Canadian visit. Thank you for making the experience a memorable one.', 5, '76.67.135.44', '2018-08-04 01:20:57', 1, '2018-08-04 01:20:57'),
(13, 4, 'Frances L', 'flee@htmail.com', '', 'Enjoyed this tour from Toronto to Niagara. Elisha and the coach driver are 5* in making the tour. Would drop the 10 min stop at the tourist shop. Waste of time no one is going to buy anything in 10 mins. Also didn\\\'t really want to go to the wine tasting  and therefore didn\\\'t enjoy this either. Loved Niagara, hornblower trip and Niagara on the lake. would have liked more time at Niagara with the opportunity to cross the river on the cable car.  Bus driver is a great driver !', 5, '76.67.135.137', '2018-07-31 20:13:29', 1, '2018-07-31 20:13:29'),
(14, 4, 'D Barrett', 'dbarrett@htmail.com', '', 'We had a great day with the tour!  We were picked up as indicated and transported to Niagara region. When we arrived at the falls, our tour guide got us connected with the Falls staff and we went directly to the boat ride bypassing the long lines! We made a couple of stops along the way back and the town of Niagara on The Lakes was very picturesque!  The only irritation with the tour were the tourists who at each stop forgot how to use their watch and were late arriving back delaying the group! This is no fault of the company. The tour guide Haroon was very pleasant and informative  adding to the experience!', 5, '76.67.135.137', '2018-07-28 23:05:15', 1, '2018-07-28 23:05:15'),
(15, 4, 'E Pratt', 'epratt@htmail.com', '', 'Brilliant day - the best thing we did on our holiday and definitely worth every penny! Our tour guide Alisha was great - very friendly and knowledgable, took very good care of all of us. Would 100% recommend to anyone visiting!', 5, '76.67.135.137', '2018-07-24 14:45:58', 1, '2018-07-24 14:45:58'),
(16, 6, 'J Menker', 'jmenker@htmail.com', '', 'Raj was an excellent guide and driver.  He went out of his way to make sure we maximized our time and had a great visit to the Niagara area.', 5, '76.67.135.137', '2018-07-22 15:00:36', 1, '2018-07-22 15:00:36'),
(17, 4, 'Ryan K.', 'rkusch@htmail.com', '', 'Excellent selection of activities spread throughout a fun-filled day.', 5, '76.67.135.137', '2018-07-21 19:35:58', 1, '2018-07-21 19:35:58'),
(18, 4, 'Robert P', 'robertp@htmail.com', '', 'Everything that was promised was delivered,  plus more. Niagara Falls was magnificent and the tour company made the whole experience memorable for all the right reasons!!', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-07-12 11:53:58', 1, '2018-07-12 11:53:58'),
(19, 4, 'A Leslie', 'aleslie@htmail.co', '', 'Excellent day trip with both guide and bus driver excellent. Lots of interesting facts to accompany the day. A minor criticism is that possibly too much was tried on the day with too many short stops - staff were reliant in bus party passengers to return to the bus at the requisite times but often this was not the case. Despite this I would recommend this tour company.', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-07-12 11:50:04', 1, '2018-07-12 11:50:04'),
(20, 4, 'A Torrens', 'atorrens@gmil.com', '', 'Such a great experience! Our tour guide Alicia was great! Very informative. Highly recommend this tour!', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-07-12 11:48:13', 1, '2018-07-12 11:48:13'),
(21, 4, 'Leyton M.', 'lmiles@htmail.com', '', 'Really enjoyed the tour.  The bus driver Haroon was excellent and Joe the tour guide was also fantastic.  His local knowledge was amazing and made the tour even more informative.  Highly recommend the tour to all.  Only improvement would be to spend more time at the falls and less stops on the way back.', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-07-05 00:36:20', 1, '2018-07-05 00:36:20'),
(22, 4, 'bernard cipriano', 'bcipriano@htmail.com', '', 'One of the best times', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-06-28 18:43:35', 1, '2018-06-28 18:43:35'),
(23, 4, 'K Bieber', 'kbieber@htmail.com', '', 'My husband and I booked this trip a week in advance and were surprised at the availability. We weren\\\'t sure what to expect, but were excited to see Niagara. The host and the driver were so much fun! They kept everything on track for time and took us to a lot of really neat places. I highly recommend this tour as it was well organized and a lot of fun!', 5, '70.54.44.218', '2018-06-26 15:36:53', 1, '2018-06-26 15:36:53'),
(24, 9, 'Brooklyn S', 'brooklyns@htmail.com', '', 'Such a fun experience! We went around 9:15 in the morning and didn’t have to wait long at all. The staff were very helpful and attentive to getting us where we needed to be. Once we were on the boat we only waited maybe 10 minutes before departing. Such a cool view of both falls and nice that they provide the ponchos! Loved all the videos and would definitely do it again! [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 20, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-21 17:44:59', 1, '2018-06-21 17:44:59'),
(25, 11, 'Michael S.', 'michaels@htmail.com', '', 'I took the fireworks cruise at 9:30 PM and had a great time. Just the drinks offered at the pier are expensive (8,50 for a beer). I can still very much recommend the cruise.[Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 21, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-21 17:41:53', 1, '2018-06-21 17:41:53'),
(26, 4, 'L Rollinson', 'lrollinson@htmail.com', '', 'The tour exceeded my expectations. Excellent service. Very entertaining tour covering far more than advertised. The tour guides wete awesome and went the extra distance. Helicopter ride definitely worth doing. Great value for money and would highly recommend', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-20 12:59:45', 1, '2018-06-20 12:59:45'),
(27, 11, 'M Bachini', 'MBachini@htmail.com', '', 'We did the nighttime fireworks tour. Great experience. Only let down was that they advertise 10 minutes worth of fireworks and it was only 5. [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 19, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-19 14:12:09', 1, '2018-06-19 14:12:09'),
(28, 9, 'B Simmons', 'bsimmons@htmail.com', '', 'Such a fun experience! We went around 9:15 in the morning and didn’t have to wait long at all. The staff were very helpful and attentive to getting us where we needed to be. Once we were on the boat we only waited maybe 10 minutes before departing. Such a cool view of both falls and nice that they provide the ponchos! Loved all the videos and would definitely do it again! [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 19, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-19 14:09:00', 1, '2018-06-19 14:09:00'),
(29, 11, 'T Skinner', 'tskinner@htmail.com', '', 'The only way to see the falls at night [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Reviews June 16, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-17 16:11:47', 1, '2018-06-17 16:11:47'),
(30, 9, 'Steve J', 'stevej@htmail.com', '', 'Top notch!', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-13 13:06:00', 1, '2018-06-13 13:06:00'),
(31, 9, 'N Zwaneveld', 'NZwaneveld@htmail.com', '', 'Geweldige boottocht naar de mist van Niagara Falls! Je gaat vrij ver naar de waterval, en zonder poncho (die je daar gratis krijgt) wordt je doorweekt. Als je kunt kiezen tussen de boottocht van Amerikaanse-zijde of deze boottocht vanaf de Canadese-zijde, dan loont het de moeite om naar de Canadese-zijde te komen. De falls is hier veel mooier te zien, en de boottocht vanaf de Canadese-zijde duurt langer en gaat verder naar de falls dan de boten van Maiden of the Mist (Amerikaanse zijde). [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 13, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-13 13:02:22', 1, '2018-06-13 13:02:22'),
(32, 6, 'David H', 'dh@htmail.com', '', 'Just a short note to say thanks to you all and Shaz in particular our guide and driver for an excellent, stress free day at Niagara. The young guy was excellent and really knew his stuff.\r\n\r\nMy one piece of advice. You Canadians need to spread out more. A population of 37m in the 2nd largest land mass in the world means you shouldn’t have traffic jams that bad.\r\n\r\nAll the best for the rest of the summer and beyond.', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-13 12:38:34', 1, '2018-06-13 12:38:34'),
(33, 9, 'G Toth', 'gtoth@htmail.com', '', 'Great experience, very friendly staff. Even with ponchos you still get wet. But we\\\'ll worth it. [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 5, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-12 14:25:18', 1, '2018-06-12 14:25:18'),
(34, 9, 'B Center', 'bcenter@htmail.com', '', 'You’re going to get soaked but damn if it isn’t amazing. They really get the boat way up close to the falls. I’ve been disappointed with touristy stuff before but this delivers. [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Reviews June 6, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-12 14:20:42', 1, '2018-06-12 14:20:42'),
(35, 9, 'J Siegal', 'jsiegal@htmail.com', '', 'Amazing and worth the money.  The view was amazing and something I suggest everyone do once in their life.  Unforgettable experience! [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Reviews June 12, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-12 14:18:47', 1, '2018-06-12 14:18:47'),
(36, 9, 'J. Bennett', 'jbennett@htmail.com', '', 'Totally worth going on the boat ride. You do get wet but the give you ponchos. It’s so fun to get up close. Seems like the American side boat ride is just the same. Seems light less crowds if you go early in the morning. [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Reviews June 6, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-12 14:14:59', 1, '2018-06-12 14:14:59'),
(37, 9, 'A. Gonzales', 'agonzales@htmail.com', '', 'This boat ride to the Canadian side of Niagara Falls was awesome!\r\nPaying was super easy with the self-serve kiosks, we didn\\\'t even have to wait in line.\r\nGetting on the boat was quick and orderly.\r\nBeing right in front of The Falls and feeling the water was exhilarating!\r\nI would do this again. [Obtained from Hornblower Boat Cruise Google Review June 11, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-12 14:06:54', 1, '2018-06-12 14:06:54'),
(38, 9, 'Kruti G.', 'krutig@htmail.com', '', 'Best tour in niagara', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-11 14:17:37', 1, '2018-06-11 14:17:37'),
(39, 9, 'P Winiecki', 'PWiniecki@htmail.com', '', 'Absolutely, Positively, No Questions Asked- MUST DO. You can not get closer to the Falls. [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review June 8, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-11 13:28:59', 1, '2018-06-11 13:28:59'),
(40, 9, 'D. Patel', 'dpatel@htmail.com', '', 'If you can cross into to Canada then definitely do so and take a Hornblower Cruise. While Maid of The Mist is great I felt that this cruise was longer and went in deeper. Overall this is a amazing experience and everyone should experience it. Pro-tip: stand in the front if you want to get drenched. [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, June 10, 2018]', 5, '70.54.52.25', '2018-06-11 13:16:25', 1, '2018-06-11 13:16:25'),
(41, 4, 'Phil W', 'philw@htmail.com', '', 'No words can explain the experience of the falls. The enjoyment was compounded by the tour guide (Alisha) and driver (Eli).  The day is very high on our experiences list, of our Round The World trip!\r\nThank you!', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-06-02 15:04:55', 1, '2018-06-02 15:04:55'),
(42, 4, 'Michael C', 'michaelc@htmail.com', '', 'Everything about our tour was meticulously planned ,and,happened as promised ,our pick up was within 1 minute of time stated,our driver explained exactly what was going to happen,and it did,needless to say the experience at the falls was one never to be forgotten,helped along by our driver/guide.  Lunch was way above expectations and the event at the Sheraton was well managed.  All-in-all a great day, and have no hesitation in recommending ToNiagara to my friends we went on a very hot day and were supplied with ample supplies of water,and there is a surprise at the end of the day \\\"say no more\\\"', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-06-02 14:13:29', 1, '2018-06-02 14:13:29'),
(43, 4, 'Reuben D.', 'reubend@htmail.com', '', 'Great day and they made it super easy to get picked up. Great communication pre-trip', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-06-01 00:40:29', 1, '2018-06-01 00:40:29'),
(44, 4, 'Jordan C', 'jordanc@htmail.com', '', 'We had a fantastic time, Alicia and Eli were great. The tour ran on time and everything was communicated clearly. ToNiagara offered immediate responses to any questions and made sure we were informed every step of the way. Would recommend to anyone considering a trip from Toronto to Niagara with no fuss.', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-31 01:31:17', 1, '2018-05-31 01:31:17'),
(45, 4, 'Romina F', 'rominaf@htmail.con', '', 'We had an amazing experience with ToNiagara tour. My husband and I usually drive every where, but we decided to take a tour bus for the first time, since it was going to be a long day, so my husband could just relax and enjoy the trip. We were picked up and dropped off nearby our appartment downtown Toronto and we spent the whole day out with them. Alicia the guide is a lot of fun, we really liked her, and our driver did a good job taking us to Niagara and back safe. They did all what they offered on the site. The buffet at the Sheraton was very good and you can still see the falls from there. I would absolutely recomend ToNiagara.', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-28 16:21:00', 1, '2018-05-28 16:21:00'),
(46, 4, 'Linda M.', 'lmcgee@htmail.com', '', 'Excellent day - fantastic tour guide Elisha - she was extremely knowledgeable, friendly and good company. She dealt with two passengers who constantly held the bus up in a patient professional manner. I was originally concerned that it was a full day with many stops but they were short stops and helped to break the day up.\r\n\r\nNiagara Falls were amazing and we were fast tracked onto the boat tour which was good. Lunch at the Sheraton was good with a plentiful buffet.\r\n\r\nThe driver was excellent as well kept us safe on a busy motorway. \r\n\r\nI would thoroughly recommend this tour and Elisha and driver (sorry forgot his name)\r\n\r\nGreat memories of Niagara Falls were made.', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-27 15:06:20', 1, '2018-05-27 15:06:20'),
(47, 4, 'Peter Moncrieff', 'pmoncrieff@htmail.com', '', 'Collected and dropped off as promised , very pleasant and informative driver . We wouldn\\\'t have seen as much had it not been for the tour . Worth every penny . Nice lunch stop and visit to the vineyard and wine tasting .', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-25 15:24:33', 1, '2018-05-25 15:24:33'),
(48, 4, 'J Wong', 'jwong@htmail.com', '', 'Unpretentious, fun and lighthearted-this was exactly what I needed when I was looking at last-minute tours to Niagara Falls.  I particularly liked that we got a lot of free time to wander the Falls and Niagara-on-the-Lake', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-25 01:24:27', 1, '2018-05-25 01:24:27'),
(49, 9, 'N Koester', 'nkoester@htmail.com', '', 'You won\\\'t stay dry, but you get a great view of the falls [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 23, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-23 17:56:04', 1, '2018-05-23 17:56:04'),
(50, 9, 'Mark A', 'marka@htmail.com', '', 'Great experience &amp; is a must when in Canada. The roar down in the water is amazing and the sound you here up top on the banks is nothing compared to it. Interesting info on the mini tour from the dock to the base of the falls itself. Top marks.[Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 15, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-22 18:15:20', 1, '2018-05-22 18:15:20'),
(51, 9, 'Greg Greavette', 'ggreavette@htmail.com', '', 'Hour wait for a 20 minute boat right on a Friday at 9am so I can only imagine how bad it could be on a busy day. Nice ride though, kids loved it. [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 21, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-22 18:01:37', 1, '2018-05-22 18:01:37'),
(52, 9, 'Tauqir A', 'tauqira@htmail.com', '', 'A MUST have experience. \r\n\r\nIn fact all the Boat Rides to the Falls are MUST to do. [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 14, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-21 15:29:57', 1, '2018-05-21 15:29:57'),
(53, 9, 'Doce Mel', 'docemel26@htmail.com', '', 'If you have the option of being able to cross the boarding into Canada and unsure which boat tour to take to see the falls look no further than the Hornblower Cruise. They offer a fast, safe, well coordinated experience into the heart of horseshoe falls. \r\n\r\nIf you have any electronics you do not want getting wet make sure to leave them with someone on dry land. They do provide ponchos - which I recommend you tie securely because when the wind blows it will lift up causing you to get even more wet. \r\n\r\nHaving a go pro around your neck during this ride makes for an excellent way to capture the greatness of this natural wonder. \r\n\r\nBe sure to have dry socks to change into if you have other activities planned the remainder of your day or book this tour as your last stop. The ideal time to visit is around 2-4pm for the warmest times as the water is freezing cold. If you want to avoid major lines do go earlier or later in the day. 10am or 4pm. \r\n\r\nThey offer a night cruise with light show and fireworks on select nights. Check their website for dates and availability. Do purchase your tickets ahead of time to ensure entrance as they do get very busy during the months of June and July.[Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 17, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-21 15:23:37', 1, '2018-05-21 15:23:37'),
(54, 9, 'John B', 'johnbr@htmail.com', '', 'You think you have seen all the view of the falls but getting in the boat gives you a whole other perspective! The crew were friendly! The poncho keeps you somewhat dry but if you are taking pictures bring waterproof camera as there is no way with an iPhone.[Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 17, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-21 15:21:14', 1, '2018-05-21 15:21:14'),
(55, 9, 'Hamyela M', 'hamyelam@htmail.com', '', '(Translated by Google) It is worth climbing the boat with the rain poncho and feeling the noise and the water and the wind generated by the falls and contemplating them. It is a beautiful and unique experience.[Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 18, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-21 15:16:12', 1, '2018-05-21 15:16:12'),
(56, 9, 'Aurela Z', 'aurelaz@htmail.com', '', 'Amazing experience ! This was my favorite thing I did while at the falls! You will definitely get wet because the cruise gets pretty close to the falls but it is worth it. I bought a plastic case to keep phone in so I could get a bunch of videos and pictures and that worked well. [Obtained from Hornblower Niagara Cruises Google Review, May 19, 2018]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-20 17:00:49', 1, '2018-05-20 17:00:49'),
(57, 4, 'Chris G.', 'chrisg@htmail.com', '', 'Had an amazing time. Tour guide was very helpful, friendly and knowledgeable. Informed us every turn we took and every road we were on of all that was coming up to see. Loved it {ToNiagara Google Review]', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-15 18:23:04', 1, '2018-05-15 18:23:04'),
(58, 4, 'R. Luckins', 'rluckins@htmail.com', '', '<p>to Niagara tour was great! The weather that day was not, it was cold windy and rainy but we still went we still had fun and the tour guide Alicia, was awesome !<br>\r\n They pick you up at your destination pretty much on time they tell you all about Toronto and surrounding areas and they take you for a little places that you would never think to go along the way.<br>\r\n They stop at gift shops to get some discounts, you get some great views,  along the way. Unfortunately that day due to the weather the boat could not go to the falls so we got to go behind the falls which was neat as well. Then they give you about 2 1/2 hours on your own around Niagara Falls to explore but just not enough time it is like Disneyland for adults and kids in Niagara Falls downtown. Then we stopped at a winery it was a very quick stop and then on the bus, we headed for home then we weâ€™re home by 7 oâ€™clock it was awesome, day too bad for the weather .  Make sure you bring an umbrella whether itâ€™s raining or hot, thereâ€™s not a lot of shelter around and less youâ€™re inside the building.<br>\r\n It was a great tour I would totally recommend it to anybody and everybody!!! [From Google Reviews]</p>', 5, '76.67.132.144', '2018-05-15 18:18:52', 1, '2018-05-15 18:18:52'),
