(103, 12, 'Julie 669', 'julie669@htmail.com', '', 'As airline crew its not often we get a whole day off in a country these days. However, this time, we were very lucky and were able to arrange a trip to Niagara Falls from Toronto. Ian could not have done more for us. He went out of his way to do everything he could to show us as much as he could and give us a wonderful day out. The highlights being the Hornblower boat ride into the falls and, topping it off, a wonderful flight over the falls in a small 4 seater plane! We then went for a charming visit to Niagara on the lake. A beautiful place to visit and we would recommend lunch at the Golf Course, it has stunning views over the lake...all in all, a wonderful day out, great value for money and a lovely host/driver. Thank you Ian. We will definetely be recommending you to all our crew and passengers, friends and family! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.27.89.204', '2018-02-05 14:59:18', 1, '2018-02-05 14:59:18'),
(104, 13, 'anonymous A', 'Anonymous@htmail.com', '', 'Niagara Falls Air Tours make every effort to ensure that their customers have the best viewing experience as possible. The pilot is very friendly and explain every details needed to make the trip enjoyable. I initially booked my air tour on Saturday a month ago. However, the sky was gray on the day of my scheduled appointment. Niagara Falls Air Tours contacted me to inform me that the tour needs to be postpone my tour. The reason is that regulations require them to fly above the clouds, which will diminished the Niagara Falls viewing. They truly want their customers to have the best experience (and get their money’s worth) rather than trying to make a quick buck. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.27.89.204', '2018-02-05 14:56:27', 1, '2018-02-05 14:56:27'),
