(131, 13, 'Tess I', 'tessi@htmail.com', '', 'Everything was organised to perfection.\r\n\r\nBooked this from the UK - great customer focus and service.\r\n\r\nBooked online, received a txt day before with confirmation directions etc.\r\n\r\nGreat service from Ian and Keith (the pilot) was exceptional.\r\n\r\nFar better than a helicopter flight.\r\n\r\nThank you Ian and Keith [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 19:47:46', 1, '2018-01-29 19:47:46'),
(132, 13, 'Zana T', 'zanat@htmail.com', '', 'I surprised my boyfriend with this plane ride for our anniversary and it was a lot of fun! Great experience. Captain Fox was very friendly. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:19:49', 1, '2018-01-29 14:19:49'),
(133, 13, 'Anonymous A', 'scaredofheights@htmail.com', '', 'My sisters and I took this plane ride above Niagara and could not have been more impressed. The pilot was great company and the view was amazing. We received amazing service all around. I would 100% take my husband back and do the ride again. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:16:53', 1, '2018-01-29 14:16:53');
INSERT INTO `tour_reviews` (`ID`, `tour_id`, `name`, `email`, `website`, `description`, `count_star`, `author_IP`, `created_on`, `status`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(134, 13, 'Jessica J', 'jessicaj@htmail.com', '', 'We called to set up a flight with Ian, and from the very beginning he was so friendly and easy to work with. When we got there he greeted us with friendly smiles and information on what our trip will be like. We met the pilot and took pictures with the plane. once in the plane it was something I will never forget-- smooth rides, friendly and informative information on what we were seeing. It was such a wonderful trip taking this plane over Niagara. WE WILL DEFINITELY DO IT AGAIN. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:12:35', 1, '2018-01-29 14:12:35'),
(135, 22, 'Scott G', 'scottg@htmail.com', '', 'had a layover in Toronto and wanted to see the falls in the short time I was there.\r\n\r\nDriving out there and back during rush hour was not practical, nor very cost efficient with the price of taxis, but then I came across the Niagara Falls Air Tours operating directly out of Billy Bishop airport in Toronto. More importantly, they offered the ability to fly out, see the falls, and be back in the city again within the space of two hours-- you can\\\'t beat that efficiency for a short visit!\r\n\r\nFrom the first moment you see the classic 1960s airplane, to the moment you\\\'re drifting over Horseshoe Falls, every part of the tour was unforgettable. This wasn\\\'t just another helicopter tour, which there are dozens of for various attractions, but a fantastic little aircraft, which has been lovingly preserved-- during the tour, the pilot even told me how he used it the week prior to pick his mother up from all the way over in the US-- to the onboard commentary about what you\\\'re seeing outside the window as you go along the shore of Lake Ontario and over Niagara Falls itself, every moment was magical, and well worth the money.\r\n\r\nIt may sound expensive at first, but when you factor in the ground transport it would take to get out to the falls for a helicopter tour, the airplane tour is well worth it, especially when you also factor in the advantage of being able to go directly out of Toronto itself, leaving more time to explore the city itself should you be on a tight schedule like I was. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:09:57', 1, '2018-01-29 14:09:57'),
(136, 13, 'Christi C', 'christic@htmail.com', '', 'I took my 14 year old daughter for her birthday celebration as she had never been on an airplane before. We got much more than what we expected! Guided tour of both American and Canadian falls, the whirlpool, the Welland canal and useful history tips and information. Smooth flight, lovely pilot. We will definitely come back again with more of our kids.', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:07:33', 1, '2018-01-29 14:07:33'),
(137, 13, 'Meaghan R.', 'meaghanr@htmail.com', '', 'Have to say it was by far one of the best plane rides ever. Myself I\\\'m very afraid to fly and Keith was really great pilot and the overall ride was amazing . For my husband it was his dream of getting up in a plane so thank Ian and keith for the best birthday my husband he will never forget [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 14:00:21', 1, '2018-01-29 14:00:21'),
(138, 12, 'Melly Q.', 'mellyq@htmail.com', '', 'the trip was amazing , it was affordable . ian is an amazing guy .. will see me again soon. xoxo melly [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 13:49:08', 1, '2018-01-29 13:49:08'),
(139, 13, 'Hillary V.', 'hillaryv@htmail.com', '', 'Our guide Keith was super knowledgeable - AMAZING way to see the falls! Awesome idea for a date or birthday gift. A truly unique, new and exciting experience - especially if you\\\'ve already seen the falls before! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 13:47:12', 1, '2018-01-29 13:47:12'),
(140, 13, 'Gloria M.', 'gloriam@htmail.com', '', 'Fully recommened, service was great, people amazing, and pilot with great experience, service on time, no delays, thank you and keep the great service [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 13:44:56', 1, '2018-01-29 13:44:56'),
(141, 12, 'Jessica W', 'jessw@htmail.com', '', 'This experience is so worth the money and dare I say it\\\'s an unforgettable memory for my friends.\r\nThe whole crew was beyond professional and it couldn\\\'t get any better with their extrodinary service! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-29 13:42:18', 1, '2018-01-29 13:42:18'),
(142, 13, 'Michelle S', 'michelles@htmail.com', '', 'Located just 15 mins from Niagara Falls, these guys were fantastic! Excellent, responsive customer service, more reasonable than the helicopter tours, 30 full mins in the air with an owner operator who knows the area well. Thank you to Ian and Keith Fox for the wonderful experience that made our trip special. Thank you for pointing out all of the geographical and historical points of interest too!!! We\\\'ll never get better shots of the Falls either! Xo.[Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:20:12', 1, '2018-01-27 14:20:12'),
(143, 13, 'V Yacheslav', 'vyacheslav@htmail.com', '', 'Extremely happy with this opportunity to fly on such plane and see beautiful Niagara from that point of view. \r\nKeith is a real pro, started flying when he was 16yo. Ian is one of the helpful and probably nicest person I have ever met. \r\nThank you for unforgettable moments! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:18:24', 1, '2018-01-27 14:18:24'),
(144, 13, 'S. Maessen', 'smaessen@htmail.com', '', 'A must do experience when you are visiting the Niagara falls!! Very friendly staff and incredible views! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:16:33', 1, '2018-01-27 14:16:33'),
(145, 13, 'Manny O', 'mannyo@yhoo.com', '', 'Very professional. The whole process was very smooth. The plane was ready to go when we got there. Highly recommended. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:04:39', 1, '2018-01-27 14:04:39'),
(146, 12, 'Shelley L', 'shelleyl@htmail.com', '', 'Our driver was so courteous, he always opened my door and checked us in at every wine tour destination. On our drive back to the hotel, he drove into a few beautiful landmarks and explained each one in detail...I would highly recommend this service to anyone..the pilot was so professional..I am terrified of heights and he made me feel so comfortable, thank you so much for an unforgettable experience. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:02:35', 1, '2018-01-27 14:02:35'),
(147, 12, 'Lisa B', 'lisab@htmail.com', '', 'Our Pilot was fantastic! Prior to our flight our pilot took pictures of us by the plane and explained what to expect during our half hour flight. The flight was narrated so we never had to guess what area we were viewing during our tour. I would highly recommend this to anyone who would love to view areas of niagara and the falls, during their visit to Niagara. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 14:00:06', 1, '2018-01-27 14:00:06'),
(148, 13, 'Adjua a', 'adjua@htmail.com', '', 'This was the highlight of our trip! Very knowledgeable pilot there was never a dull moment. The views were beautiful! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 13:58:06', 1, '2018-01-27 13:58:06'),
(149, 13, 'Paige M', 'paigem@htmail.com', '', 'This was the highlight of our trip! Very knowledgeable pilot there was never a dull moment. The views were beautiful! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 13:55:51', 1, '2018-01-27 13:55:51'),
(150, 13, 'Kamila K', 'kamilak@htmail.com', '', 'Keith and Ian definitively made our experience an unforgettable and one of a kind, especially since it was my bf\\\'s first time on a plane. They made us feel very special by providing a VIP type of feel with first class customer service, BIG THANK YOU! \r\nBeen to Niagara over 40+ times but never like this [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 13:53:51', 1, '2018-01-27 13:53:51'),
(151, 12, 'Annette D', 'annetted@htmail.com', '', 'We had a fabulous time and felt very well cared for throughout our day. I needed a little extra help with due to a knee injury and everything worked out better than we could have hoped for. Would definitely recommend and even return if we were back up that way! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 13:51:16', 1, '2018-01-27 13:51:16'),
(152, 12, 'Jenny K', 'jennyk@htmail.com', '', 'Loved the helicopter tour and boat tour of Niagara falls. It was breathtaking :) And winery was amazing as well. Thank you for the wonderful time [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:17:00', 1, '2018-01-27 03:17:00'),
(153, 13, 'Prashant G', 'prashantg@htmail.com', '', 'When I booked it, I assumed it was a helicopter ride which is what everyone seems to do. When we got to the airport (yes you need go to a proper airport) and found the hanger, we realized it was a single engine small airplane !! It was a neatly maintained but an old airplane. Best part was there were nobody else than me and my wife in the ride. I got super excited (not so my wife :) ) to sit next to the pilot. \r\n\r\nCompared to the helicopter ride (which my friends said was like 13 minute) this was a 30 minute ride. The ride was very smooth and pilot was knowledgeable and informative about various spots around Niagara falls. \r\n\r\nThey also matched the Groupon price when I mentioned it to him. BTW - If you are doing Groupon or likes, please make sure that you have talked to the guys before you reach there. You need to call well in advance and reserve your seats. \r\n\r\nOverall, I loved it. Was our first experience with a single engine plane but felt worth every penny. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:14:12', 1, '2018-01-27 03:14:12'),
(154, 13, 'martha b', 'marthab@htmail.com', '', 'Great company. Ian helped me to coordinate my flight as the weather was not contributing. \r\nKeith, the pilot gave us interesting info while flying and made our flying experience unforgettable. \r\nLoved it! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:10:57', 1, '2018-01-27 03:10:57'),
(155, 12, 'Kathi E', 'kathie@htmail.com', '', 'I always recommend a tour guide over going on your own. Don\\\'t have to worry about tickets or parking or lunch. Very nice way to celebrate our 20 year anniversary. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:08:13', 1, '2018-01-27 03:08:13'),
(156, 12, 'jeanne c', 'jeannec@htmail.com', '', 'I took my parents to the tour and they loved it. The weather helped and flight was just perfect. Friendly staff and beautiful air plane! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:04:17', 1, '2018-01-27 03:04:17'),
(157, 13, 'xylo g', 'xylog@htmail.com', '', 'Where do I start!!! From the moment my friends and I boarded the plane to the moment we disembarked we were amazed! Both Ian and Keith made our flight a memorable one. The sights we saw took our breath away. To view Niagara Falls from the air is something else! It is a definite must do! Words cannot describe our experience in the air. Everything was absolutely AMAZING!!! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 03:02:30', 1, '2018-01-27 03:02:30'),
(158, 12, 'Charlitah H', 'charlitah@htmail.com', '', 'EVERYTHING about the one day tour was awesome! It was well organized and Ian was a remarkable host. I would do it again when given the opportunity! I loved it, me and my 3 friends whom joined me! Not one complaint! Ian provided a WIFI hotspot, water, fresh fruit and an unforgettable experience! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:59:39', 1, '2018-01-27 02:59:39'),
(159, 12, 'Sam J', 'samj@htmail.com', '', 'I had such an amazing experience on the tour. Professional and very friendly. I couldn\\\'t have asked for more.[Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:53:12', 1, '2018-01-27 02:53:12'),
(160, 13, 'nnn d', 'nnnd@htmail.com', '', 'Amazing tour! Very friendly and approachable driver, Plane tour was the best! Recommend it to everyone. [Reviewed by TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:51:42', 1, '2018-01-27 02:51:42'),
(161, 13, 'Peter E.', 'petere@htmail.com', '', 'First time on a plane. We had a great time. The fall look a lot better from the air then is dose from the ground. Definitely worth it. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:48:44', 1, '2018-01-27 02:48:44'),
(162, 13, 'Rich K', 'richk@htmail.com', '', 'A wonderful flight over the falls and surrounding area on a perfectly clear day! The stunning views that our pilot Keith was able to provide will be forever etched in our minds. Worth every cent! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:46:48', 1, '2018-01-27 02:46:48'),
(163, 13, 'David C', 'davidc@htmail.com', '', 'We only had a few hours in the Niagara peninsula for our visit, and it was my wife\\\'s birthday. I decided that instead of going to the Falls themselves, we would take a 1/2 hour flight to see them from the air. What a great decision. My wife was very excited until she saw the plane, and realised it was just a 4-seater. However, this trepidation was short-lived when Keith, the pilot, took the time to explain how best to be a passenger in it, and after a spectacular flight with lots of interesting information from Keith, she had what she called the MOST AMAZING BIRTHDAY PRESENT... EVER!!! We highly recommend this for a special occasion, or just to see the Falls and the area with a birds eye view. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-27 02:44:34', 1, '2018-01-27 02:44:34'),
(164, 12, 'Carolyn D.', 'carolynd@htmail.com', '', 'Ian was an amazing host and guide. For the price of our ticket we got to stroll along the top of the falls, take a boat ride, a plane ride, enjoyed a lovely lunch at a golf club in the lake and the visited a winery and did some wine tasting. We will recommend this excursion to family and friends. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 19:43:22', 1, '2018-01-26 19:43:22'),
(165, 13, 'Kaitlyn A.', 'kaitlyna@htmail.com', '', 'Once my best friend and I found where to go (the hanger isn\\\'t well marked- but people are nice enough to point it out), Ian met up with us to talk with us before our flight. Amazing service. The ride itself was gorgeous and worth every penny to see such a beautiful landmark from a different view. Our pilot was helpful in pointing out all of the places that were below us as well as telling us about the origins of the plane. It was an amazing experience and I would definitely do it again! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 17:03:03', 1, '2018-01-26 17:03:03'),
(166, 12, 'Petjulla A', 'Petjullaa@htmail.com', '', 'We\\\'ve had an amazing time with my colleagues and our guid Ian took great care of us! Highlight is definitely the flight over Niagara\\\'s and surroundings and the stunning view from the sky. A huge thank you for this trip!! :) [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 16:54:23', 1, '2018-01-26 16:54:23'),
(167, 13, 'Sonya T.', 'sonyat@htmail.com', '', 'I was happily surprised to have a private tour with only the pilot, my boyfriend and I. For some reason I thought the plane would be a bigger one and there were a few other people with us, but no. The flight went smoothly (great take off and landing). The pilot has interesting things to say about the region. I would recommend to anybody. Totally worth the price. This was a nice surprise gift for my boyfriend\\\'s bd. :)[Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 16:51:11', 1, '2018-01-26 16:51:11'),
(168, 13, 'Anne C.', 'annec@htmail.com', '', 'What an amazing experience, a must do in Niagara! Booking was very easy and quick on their website. Arrived at the airport, flight let on time, views from above are breathtaking! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 16:49:02', 1, '2018-01-26 16:49:02'),
(169, 13, 'Yun L.', 'yunlinz@htmail.com', '', 'It\\\'s a excellent tour especially the 30minutes air tour, I like it very much. I highly recommend!!!! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 16:38:55', 1, '2018-01-26 16:38:55'),
(170, 13, 'Gonz G.', 'gonzgarg@htmail.com', '', 'What an amazing day! Ian is Just the graetest guy, had an awesome day everyone should try this tour at least once. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 16:36:32', 1, '2018-01-26 16:36:32'),
(171, 12, 'Craig G', 'craigg@htmail.com', '', 'The weather turned out nice for the flight over the region. Especially enjoyed the flight over the falls. Niagara Falls in the winter is a beautiful sight! Thank you Ian for looking after things and making sure all went well. And a big thanks to our pilot, Keith, who made sure we saw and learned as much about the area as we could. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-26 15:47:56', 1, '2018-01-26 15:47:56'),
(172, 12, 'Eres Z', 'eresz@htmail.com', '', 'We went to Canada for 2 weeks and this was the highlight of the trip. All was organized perfectly, the plane is an amazing experience. Pick up from Toronto was very convenience. Not so cheap, but worth every moment. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:59:46', 1, '2018-01-24 14:59:46'),
(173, 13, 'Mike F', 'mikef@htmail.com', '', 'I can\\\'t speak highly enough about this company. Ian was great to work with in scheduling our flight and the pilot, Mr.\r\nFox did an amazing job giving us details as we flew over things.\r\n\r\nI highly recommend this for anyone wanting to see the falls and area from a breath taking perspective. Our teenager loved the flight and it was her favorite part of our 10 day vacation! Beautiful pictures and worth every penny! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:53:03', 1, '2018-01-24 14:53:03'),
(174, 12, 'Marcela B', 'marcelab@htmail.com', '', 'I\\\'m an flight attendant andbhave done plenty of tours world wide and I couldn\\\'t recommend this one more! Very organized, gives um time for everything, and the flight over niagara falls leaves you speechless! Definitely go for it. [Reviewed on TripAdvisors]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:50:00', 1, '2018-01-24 14:50:00'),
(175, 13, 'naiana f', 'naianaf222@htmail.com', '', 'Awesome Experience! Ian was great and very kind as well I would recomend this tour to anyone visiting the area. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:45:46', 1, '2018-01-24 14:45:46'),
(176, 12, 'Martina R.', 'martinar@htmail.com', '', 'Excellent tour thanks to our guide Ian. He was so friendly, prompt and super organized. Would definitely recommend it to family and friends. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:15:18', 1, '2018-01-24 14:15:18'),
(177, 12, 'Nik S', 'nikshak711@htmail.com', '', 'Ian was accommodating and helpful. There were scheduling issues from both sides and he was laid back about it . Ian was nice overall, and answered all my questions. \r\nHe also provided a lot of extra perks for the ride to Niagara and back to Toronto (such as fruits, water, phone chargers, wifi).\r\nI would recommend this excursion to anyone as it was pretty cool to go in a plane and see that amazing view, go on the boat ride, have a lunch in the Niagara-on-the-lake area and then have a wine tasting :) [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 14:12:35', 1, '2018-01-24 14:12:35'),
(178, 8, 'Allen O', 'alleno@htmail.com', '', 'I went to them to pop the question to my girlfriend and it was the perfect place to do it!  The staff were amazing anc accomodating.  The view where/when I proposed is when i was at the top of the Niagara Falls.  It\\\'s breathtaking bird\\\'s eye view of the falls which definitely made that moment more magical and memorable.  I would go and do this again on a different event.  Highly recommended!!!', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-24 00:00:24', 1, '2018-01-24 00:00:24'),
(179, 13, 'julie m', 'juliem@htmail.com', '', 'This was a surprise gift for my husband for our 5th Anniversary! We both loved it. It was great value and fun! Will definitely do it again! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 23:22:14', 1, '2018-01-23 23:22:14'),
(180, 12, 'Kare B', 'karebear@htmail.com', '', 'We did this for my husband\\\'s birthday. It was definitely what I expected and more. \r\n\r\nWe first we picked up in a luxury party bus. Met some some greatpeople on the tour who were from all over the world. We have people from U.K., Asia Australia and other part Europe. We expense Niagara Falls on land/boat/air. All three is breathless. Although we have lives in Toronto all our lives, this is something we have never experience. \r\nThis all inclusive tour is fun and adventurous. Will definitely recommend!!! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 23:19:03', 1, '2018-01-23 23:19:03'),
(181, 12, 'Julia D', 'juliad@htmail.com', '', 'That was an amazing experience and perfect day for little price! Everything was professionally organized. Ian made our day full of emotions and joy! I\\\'ll definitely repeat this experience one more time coz Niagara is differently beautiful in all seasons! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 17:20:05', 1, '2018-01-23 17:20:05'),
(182, 13, 'Barton Bears', 'bartonbears@htmail.com', '', 'The old hangar wasn\\\'t the most reassuring introduction to this company but the highly experienced pilot (who recently delivered a light plane to Perth, Australia) inspired great confidence and Cessnas are reliable workhorses. The flight was smooth and the pilot\\\'s comments gave context to what we were seeing. In total there were three passes over the falls so we both had excellent views. We also had great views over St Catharines, Niagara Falls, Niagara-on-the-Lake, the Wellend Canal, Fort George and Fort Niagara (where I half expected US anti-aircraft fire!) and the vast vineyards and wineries of the area. We thought the trip was great value, having obtained it for half price through Travelzoo! Highly recommended way to see the Niagara region. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 17:17:56', 1, '2018-01-23 17:17:56'),
(183, 12, 'Georgina F', 'georginaf@htmail.com', '', 'This tour honestly was one of the best tours I’ve ever done, working for an airline and seeing the world I have done many tours but this one is by far the best. Ian was fantastic and so accommodating, such a lovely and warm man. The transport was comfortable with lots of added extras, phone chargers, wifi, fruit, wipes, plastic cups for enjoying the wine after the winery tour... Ian really did have everything covered for a fantastic trip! The whole day ran so smoothly thanks to Ian. Will recommend to everyone visiting Toronto! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 17:13:50', 1, '2018-01-23 17:13:50'),
(184, 12, 'Anonymous A', 'hoey154@htmail.com', '', 'The whole experience of our day was great, from the bus journey with TONNES of fruit and water, to Ian our amazing tour guide who was very easy to talk to and super lovely. Niagra was amazing and the trip to the winery was something special...there ice wine is a MUST try! \r\n\r\nAmazing tour with an AMAZING guide!!!\r\nThank you Ian :))', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 17:12:02', 1, '2018-01-23 17:12:02'),
(185, 22, 'Linda R.', 'lindar@htmail.com', '', 'We were very impressed with the service and personal attention we recieved from Ian as had everything arranged everything from the Hotel door to the Aircraft. We had beautiful panoramic views of the wineries as we flew around the lake shore back to Toronto. Flying over St Catherine’s and the Welland Canel Our Pilot Keith impressed us with his calm professionalism. The flight ended with a special view flying around the CN tower before landing at Toronto Island Airport.\r\nA very special 36 minutes we will never forget.\r\nCan not recommend this highly enough – wish we could give then a 6th star [Reviewed on Trip Advisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 17:09:51', 1, '2018-01-23 17:09:51'),
(186, 13, 'Martin W', 'martinw@htmail.com', '', 'What an amazing experience - communication was brilliant and directions easy to find. The flight was awesome what an experience and our pilot was so informative and helpful. Can not recommend this company and the experience enough. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 16:06:28', 1, '2018-01-23 16:06:28'),
(187, 13, 'Samantha L.', 'samanthal@htmail.com', '', 'We arrived early and our pilot, Keith was there to greet us. After a quick pre-flight briefing, we were on our way, just two of us and the pilot for an amazing 30mins flight over Niagara Falls, St. Catharines, Niagara on the Lake and the river and hydro dams.\r\nIt was an unforgettable experience with a very knowledgeable and talented pilot. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 16:02:36', 1, '2018-01-23 16:02:36'),
(188, 13, 'aggie pino', 'aggiepino@htmail.com', '', 'I took the Niagara Falls Airplane tour where the pilot took us on a 30-minute flight around Niagara Falls. We flew past the falls three times and had great views of the surrounding area. Since I went at the beginning of November, it was really cool to see some of the landscape changing colors! \r\n\r\nThankfully, the weather on the day that we flew was clear. I really enjoyed the beautiful views, and I was able to get some good shots with my DSLR. Photographers wanting to get really clear shots should consider the glare on the windows and the exterior of the aircraft, but the Cessna 180 they use has decently sized windows for unobstructive views.\r\n\r\nThe pilot also gives great information about different landmarks seen on the ground so it was also an educational experience!\r\n\r\nI highly recommend this for anyone looking for an aerial experience in Niagara. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 15:35:26', 1, '2018-01-23 15:35:26'),
(189, 13, 'Kenesha A', 'keneshaa@htmail.com', '', 'I booked a tour last minute for me and my two young daughters while on a winter vacation to Niagara Falls. Ian was in contact with me almost immediately after my booking. He said there was a snowstorm coming through and we wouldn’t be able to fly on the date I’d chosen. But he was in contact with me every day since then, monitoring the weather. As soon as we had a window of opportunity when the storm cleared, he got us on a flight. The flight itself was amazing! It lasted 30 minutes and the pilot was very knowledgeable and informative. The views were beautiful! Definitely a once-in-a-lifetime experience! [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 15:30:49', 1, '2018-01-23 15:30:49'),
(190, 13, 'Watford ih', 'watfordih@htmail.com', '', 'The tour is twice the length of time as the Helicopter tour. Only 2 or three passngers. They can usually arrange for just two passengers in the plane as there are not many single bookings. We crossed over the falls no less than 3 times and the pilot was extremely helpful pointing things out to us. Soooo much better than the helicopter tours. [Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-23 15:27:35', 1, '2018-01-23 15:27:35'),
(191, 4, 'Jane T', 'Janet@htmail.com', '', 'Great Day - good value for many....company took our late booking and all arrangements were clear and easy to follow.', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2018-01-05 03:29:30', 1, '2018-01-05 03:29:30'),
(192, 17, 'Vera W.', 'veraw@htmail.com', '', 'Wanted to see the lights, so I asked for an afternoon pickup for us.  A van came and picked us up and drove us to the falls, we went to Clifton hill and played some games, then ate at the Boston Pizza there.  The we drove up and down the street looking at the christmas lights which were very pretty.  I loved this, hope to make it a family tradition.', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2017-12-17 14:26:46', 1, '2017-12-17 14:26:46'),
(193, 16, 'P Legree', 'plegree@htmail.com', '', 'We wanted to see the Falls in the winter, but it is cold so we didn\\\'t want to do an entire day tour so we did the half day one instead.  Did the Journey Behind the Falls (the water is very cold!!!) then had some warm lunch and went home.  The kids are off for the holidays so this was a quick and easy way to spend some family time!', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2017-12-17 14:22:58', 1, '2017-12-17 14:22:58'),
(194, 14, 'B Poulin', 'bpoulin@htmail.com', '', 'Haroon picked us up and drive us to Niagara Falls and we had a great time.  Falls, then lunch then the casino.  Great evening!', 5, '67.70.65.190', '2017-12-16 23:25:11', 1, '2017-12-16 23:25:11'),
(195, 7, 'M Abboud', 'mabboud@htmail.com', '', 'Great trip, I wanted to just see the falls so I couldn\\\'t take the bus tour.  They picked me at my AirBnb in Toronto and took me to see the Falls.  It was great trip.', 5, '70.54.47.224', '2017-12-16 13:26:57', 1, '2017-12-16 13:26:57'),
(196, 6, 'Kayla S', 'klocke@htmail.com', '', 'I was only in Canada for 2 days, I don\\\'t know if I will ever be back so I needed to see Niagara Falls, I didn\\\'t have much time so I saw this tour option on ToNiagara website, it was great!  The Hornblower Boat Cruise was finished for the season but I did the Journey Behind The Falls instead, had lunch, took some pictures and went to the airport.  I\\\'m glad this option was available!', 5, '70.54.47.224', '2017-12-14 13:58:32', 1, '2017-12-14 13:58:32'),
(197, 8, 'A Southman', 'asouthman@htmail.com', '', 'After a long search I finally purchased a ticket for the Helicopter ride!  This was the lowest price I could find on the internet and it\\\'s well worth  it!  It\\\'s first come first served so go early.  The ride is around 10 minutes and was a once in a lifetime experience.  The pictures I took were amazing.  Well worth the money would definitely recommend! 5/5', 5, '70.54.47.224', '2017-12-14 13:46:12', 1, '2017-12-14 13:46:12'),
(198, 4, 'D King', 'dking@htmail.com', '', 'This is my 4th time seeing Niagara Falls, I love to go in the winter.  It is such a magical place.', 5, '70.54.47.224', '2017-12-14 13:38:25', 1, '2017-12-14 13:38:25'),
(199, 26, 'George I', 'girving@htmail.com', '', 'It\\\'s nearly December and the weather is still amazing!!!  We took advantage of that and went on a lovely tour of niagara falls.  \r\nHighlights:\r\nThe Falls....of course\r\nThe whirlpool was cool to see and the rapids\r\nWinery tasting was great\r\nThe fact we didn\\\'t have to drive or do anything was the best part really!  I\\\'d recommend this tour to anyone and everyone!', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-29 16:31:18', 1, '2017-11-29 16:31:18'),
(200, 25, 'H. Gould', 'hgould@htmail.com', '', 'This was a really really good tour!  Food was good, I think I went on the only day in the month there were fireworks so I lucked out there.  Recommend highly', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-29 14:05:35', 1, '2017-11-29 14:05:35'),
(201, 7, 'Steve J.', 'sjohnson@htmail.com', '', 'Great trip.  Excellent driver and host. Would do it again!', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-27 13:25:38', 1, '2017-11-27 13:25:38'),
(202, 24, 'K Logerhead', 'klogerhead@htmail.com', '', 'Perfect!!  That is all I can say, the trip was absolutely everything I expected and more! Everyone should go at least once in their lives', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-27 13:22:20', 1, '2017-11-27 13:22:20'),
(203, 8, 'K Dickerson', 'kdickerson@htmail.com', '', 'I had to scramble to get a helicopter ride after the other tour operator cancelled on me, and i really appreciated the \\\"no reservation\\\" policy of Niagara Helicopters. It can be a little confusing as to what you are supposed to do, and the line can be up to an hour, but it is fun to watch the copters take off. We were fortunate that being a party of two, they pulled us out of line to fill a helicopter, and our wait was less than 15 minutes. They move you in and out fast as they have multiple helicopters loading and taking off, but the crew is great and efficient. It is a little hard to be warm and fuzzy when it is so loud and windy and the crew has headphones on, so I don\\\'t know why people are dinging them for politeness. I thought they were great, and I really appreciated the flexibility of being able to show up when we wanted to. The flight was beautiful, and yes, it was short, but really, compared to most helicopter flights, it was fairly cheap, and what more do you want to see? You get a great view of the falls.  I hated being shoved into the picture buying room at the end, but hey, that is what all of the attractions do, so it is no biggie. I highly recommend them, and look for coupons on line, or at the hotel tour desks. I also recommend doing it towards the end of your trip if you did the falls from both sides and as extensively as we did, because it is cool to see from the air all of the places that you went and know what you are looking at. [reviewed on Google Plus]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-24 17:33:57', 1, '2017-11-24 17:33:57'),
(204, 24, 'C Khan', 'ckhan@htmail.com', '', 'Great great tour and tour guide. There was much free time to spend doing other things around the Falls  and in Niagara on the Lake. Haroon was excellent and provided a great narrative on the drive from Toronto. The Winery tasting as better than I expected.  I recommend this tour!!!', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-21 03:31:24', 1, '2017-11-21 03:31:24'),
(205, 27, 'J Uchida', 'juchida@htmail.com', '', 'It was a great tour, unfortunately no fireworks but the lights were amazing and the buffet dinner was better than expected.', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-20 13:51:13', 1, '2017-11-20 13:51:13'),
(206, 18, 'D Schmidt', 'dschmidt@htmail.com', '', 'Hello, we came down here to see the Falls then go to Ripley\\\'s Believe it or Not and then go to the Casino.  It was a very fun trip, we are happy with the results', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-20 13:46:32', 1, '2017-11-20 13:46:32'),
(207, 24, 'Eliza Besinger', 'ebesinger@htmail.com', '', 'Great trip, worth the money', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-19 19:36:32', 1, '2017-11-19 19:36:32'),
(208, 15, 'Priya P', 'ppersaud@htmail.com', '', 'This was  a fairly easy tour forward Tour for ToNiagara.  We saw Niagara Falls then went on the boat cruise and stayed at the casino! Ride went smoothly we paid for our boat tickets in advance so we didn\\\'t have to wait in any line (the line was pretty short anyways). Then we stayed at the hoel over night.  Great weekend out with my friends!', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-19 19:32:52', 1, '2017-11-19 19:32:52'),
(209, 26, 'J Asiweh', 'jasiweh@htmail.com', '', 'It rained....that dampened out spirits a little bit, without the rain the trip was perfect, well planned great tour guide and very long tour for the price!  I enjoyed Niagara-on-the-Lake, it\\\'s a very quiet place, walking around there was peaceful.  I thought the floral clock would be bigger.  It\\\'s nice to hear about the history of the region and it\\\'s significance in Canadian history.', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-18 23:42:46', 1, '2017-11-18 23:42:46'),
(210, 6, 'Deena Chevalier', 'dchevalier@htmail.com', '', 'Just a short trip with the kids.  Ordered a vehicle to seat 4 people.  I should have upgraded to the SUV in hindsight, nobody ever wants to sit in the middle!  Either way went on the Hornblower boat and wen to clifton hill to a haunted house...which wasnt that haunted to be honest with you.  Then came back home. Great trip with kids, keep it short and busy!', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-18 23:36:47', 1, '2017-11-18 23:36:47'),
(211, 24, 'nicole wisemann', 'nwiseman@htmail.com', '', 'Juuuuuust got back from today\\\'s tour and it was amazing!  It wasn\\\'t even that cold and it\\\'s November!  So we went to Niagara Falls, I brought another sweater with me which I think helped a lot.  There is a lot of mist so another sweater is a good idea.  The we went and saw the rapids and the floral clock and the world\\\'s smallest church.  We basically saw everthing there was to see.  The we tasted some wine and here I am almost home!  Great tour guide and the trip went smoothly.  Awesome tour so glad I did it!', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-17 23:44:37', 1, '2017-11-17 23:44:37'),
(212, 14, 'Clifford Burrows', 'cburrows@htmail.com', '', 'We had 4 people to take a tour but opted for the SUV because 4 grown men in a Lincoln Town Car would not be comfortable!  So an SUV came to pick us up, we did the tour, saw the falls and Niagara on the lake and came back.  Wine was great, Pilliteri is a good winery to visit.', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-17 23:38:44', 1, '2017-11-17 23:38:44'),
(213, 21, 'Rich Griffin', 'rgriffin@htmail.com', '', 'Our Rotary Club wanted to see Niagara Falls and go to Niagara-on-the-Lake (they really just wanted to go to a winery!).  Anyways, we booked this tour months in advance to make sure we got a bus.  Customer service answered all my questions, which was nice of them.  We went on the tour, Niagara Falls cannot be explained in words its magnificent.  And then we went to the Pilliteri and 20 Bees wineries and that was wonderful.  We learned so much about wine and purchased a lot.  Fun time had by all.  Thank you toniagara', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-17 16:11:17', 1, '2017-11-17 16:11:17'),
(214, 7, 'Sumar K', 'sumark@htmail.com', '', 'I didn\\\'t want to go on a bus, so I went with a private tour.  A Lincon Town car came and picked us up.  We spent most of our time in Clifton Hill, we rode the skywheel and did the dinosaur mini putt course, which was actually kind of hard!  Then we ate at Boston Pizza and went home.  Kids had a great time, our vehicle came on time and was very clean.  Would highly recommend to others who have kids with short attention spans.....do the private tour, it\\\'s less stressful.', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-17 16:04:57', 1, '2017-11-17 16:04:57'),
(215, 19, 'Chuck Mac', 'cmac@htmail.com', '', 'I booked this tour through the website!  Easy booking, bus came to pick us up, spent a little time in Niagara and more time in wine country then came back home.  Well worth it!', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-17 15:52:52', 1, '2017-11-17 15:52:52'),
(216, 27, 'Ginny Chung', 'gchung@htmail.com', '', 'The weather was actually warmer than I had expected!  The tour was great, the food was good, it\\\'s a buffet so there\\\'s lots of selection and the view is perfect.  There were no fireworks but the falls were lit up.  I loved it.  Definitely want to take the trip in the day next time.', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-11-16 18:39:43', 1, '2017-11-16 18:39:43'),
(217, 6, 'Ryan Chapman', 'rchapman@htmail.com', '', 'It\\\'s hard to find something to complain about with this tour!   Everything went great, got an early flight to catch so we just wanted to see Niagara Falls for a quick get in and get out.  Which we did, but we also got on the boat which made the day for the kids.  We were dropped off at the airport ontime so ya if you are pressed for time this tour is perfect', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-16 00:58:03', 1, '2017-11-16 00:58:03'),
(218, 26, 'Linda Maitland', 'lmaitland@htmail.com', '', 'The weather was just how I like it....BRISK!  I must say I was not expecting this trip to be so fun, but we had a great tour group and the guide Alicia was fantastic.  There is so much to see and do in Niagara Falls, I think i\\\'d need a week just to fit it all in, but this ToNiagara Tour covered A LOT of attractions.  The best one was the Hornblower boat, you go right upto the falls, the noise is something you won\\\'t forget.  You will need to wear a comfortable shoe because there is a lot of walking on the tour and you want to keep your feet dry and comfy.  All in all great tour, great memories.', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-15 21:10:43', 1, '2017-11-15 21:10:43'),
(219, 24, 'benny shaw', 'bshaw@htmail.com', '', 'I would highly recommend this tour.', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-15 18:21:44', 1, '2017-11-15 18:21:44'),
(220, 24, 'Bethany Jarrett', 'jarrett@htmail.com', '', 'I think we were last to be picked up for the tour (we were in Oakville).  Highlights of the trip:  Hornblower boat was spectacular, it really goes right up to the falls!  Winery tasting was lovely as well as Niagara on the lake.   Last but not least, the buffet was better than I thought!  It had a great view of the falls which added to the atmosphere.  Great tour, it\\\'s a little long but that just makes it a better bang for your buck, you will be tired when you get back home!', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-13 13:39:13', 1, '2017-11-13 13:39:13'),
(221, 26, 'Wally O', 'wallyo@htmail.com', '', 'I thoroughly enjoyed this trip. It is very well paced. I really liked the Niagara-on-the-Lake portion of the tour, it was so charming and a real trip back in time!. Obviously the Niagara Falls are magnificent. The best part of the trip was taking the boat right upto the falls, the noise is so loud! For anyone travelling, i\\\'d recommend the buffet, it\\\'s good and takes the stress out of finding a somewhat healthy eating option.  The tour guide Aleesha was very funny and knowledgable.  This was  a great tour!', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-13 13:32:02', 1, '2017-11-13 13:32:02'),
(222, 26, 'Waled Sayed', 'wsayed@htmail.com', '', 'Went on a tour a couple of days ago and loved it!  Weather was a little brisk, but the magnificence of the falls made up for it and the wine at the end really warmed us up!  Great trip', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-12 19:21:21', 1, '2017-11-12 19:21:21'),
(223, 27, 'Timona Lee', 'tlee@htmail.com', '', 'This is one of the longer tours I have ever taken and I thoroughly enjoyed it!  Niagara Falls in the evening was magical, I should have went in the summer for the firecrackers but the lights on the falls made it just a good!  Dinner was great, everything was great, would recommend highly.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 16:08:12', 1, '2017-11-12 16:08:12'),
(224, 7, 'Tim Matsuchenko', 'tmatsuchenko@htmail.com', '', 'Private tour is always the best choice I feel.  You can do as you please, go where you like and eat what you want on your own schdule.  The tour was good, very nice, very clean in Niagara Falls.  We went to see the Skylon Tower, nowhere close to as high as the CN Tower but nice view.  Then went to Clifton Hill.  The children were scared with the Nightmare House, it is very dark but fun.  Then we went mini putt and home.  Good time, Niagara has a lot to do for kids.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 15:59:22', 1, '2017-11-12 15:59:22'),
(225, 19, 'Wayne Chang', 'wchang@htmail.com', '', 'My in-laws came from overseas and wanted to see Niagara Falls and go to the Casino.  So that\\\'s what we did!  We loaded into a minibus, got picked up and taken to Niagara Falls.  The bus arrived ontime, inlaws loved the Falls and really liked Casino Niagara, the restaurant in there is amazing.  We then went to a local winery and tasted wine and bought some too.  Everyone had fun so it was a great little adventure.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 15:48:57', 1, '2017-11-12 15:48:57'),
(226, 21, 'Jai Matsui', 'jmatsui@htmail.com', '', 'We have a group of 37 and are touring the world visiting religious churches, we went to Israel and then Italy, on our way back home to the USA we stopped over for 1 day in Canada.  We didn\\\'t have a lot of time but you can\\\'t go to Canada without seeing the Niagara Falls, so we looking for a tour but it was almost impossible to find one on short notice!  We finally booked a private tour with ToNiagara, which would allow us to see Niagara Falls and then be dropped of for our afternoon flight.  I\\\'m glad they sent a bigger bus because all of our luggage never would have fit!  We saw the Falls, went on the Journey Behind the Falls, which was quite thrilling then saw the whirlpool and the floral clock.  All the flights made us exhausted but we got to the airport in one piece!  Took lots of photos i\\\'m so glad that we were able to see the falls!  Must thank ToNiagara for going the extra mile to make that happen!', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 15:43:26', 1, '2017-11-12 15:43:26'),
(227, 4, 'Joe Quincy', 'jquincy@htmail.com', '', 'The bus picked us up from our hotel in Toronto at around 8:45AM, there\\\'s a little traffic coming out of the city, after picking up more passengers we arrived in Niagara Falls at around 11:30.  Right when you arrive the Niagara Falls hits you!  Such a spectacular site, it\\\'s huge and thunderous and everything I imagined.  Then we went on the boat ride which was the highlight of my trip.  After that we breaked for lunch and a stroll around, then went off to Niagara-on-the-Lake.   The floral clock was just that......a large clock embedded with flowers!  Since we went in November i\\\'m sure the flowers are more brilliantly colored in the summer months.  then off to Niagara-on-the-Lake and a winery.  I was very impressed with the tour, it was very well planned and we got to see a lot of sites.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 14:38:37', 1, '2017-11-12 14:38:37'),
(228, 15, 'Billie Jackson', 'bjackson@htmail.com', '', 'I know understand why so many people get married here!  It\\\'s beautiful, not only the Falls but wine country as well.  Thank you ToNiagara the tour was great, the vehicle was clean and picked us up on time, not much more we could ask for!', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 14:34:35', 1, '2017-11-12 14:34:35'),
(229, 25, 'Diane Moore', 'dmoore@htmail.com', '', 'Truly magnificent!  That\\\'s all I can say.  Haroon (our guide) was full of interesting information and funny tidbits.  Great tour, I highly recommend.  Make sure you check the dates for fireworks, they are seasonal so it\\\'s hit or miss in the winter months.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 14:32:07', 1, '2017-11-12 14:32:07'),
(230, 24, 'Tim Mccallister', 'tmccallister@htmail.com', '', 'My wife came for the Falls, I came for the wine!  We both left satisfied!   This tour packs in A LOT of sites, there\\\'s something for everybody.  We ordered the buffet which was good food and a wonderful view.   Wine tasting was great, I\\\'d recommend the Ice Wine for anyone who is interested.  We will be back again next year to take the evening tour!', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 14:29:44', 1, '2017-11-12 14:29:44'),
(231, 26, 'Faith Evans', 'fevans@htmai.com', '', 'Took this trip in November, the weather was cold! But Niagara Falls was beautiful. The boat cruise was still operational and that was the highlight of the tour for me! Very happy about the organization of the trip, we got to stay and see all the attractions in one day. I would recommend that if you are going in the winter wear a warm coat and comfortable shoes. Trip is well worth the money.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-12 14:23:56', 1, '2017-11-12 14:23:56'),
(232, 8, 'Michelle B', 'mbehie@htmail.com', '', 'Incredible!!! [Reviewed on Google Plus]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-11-10 19:40:57', 1, '2017-11-10 19:40:57'),
(233, 26, 'Ashok Jain', 'ajain@htmail.com', '', 'Our Guide Shahzaib was very warm, positive, energetic guy, he did an excellent job, big thank you to him and Nick at reservation center.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-06 19:42:45', 1, '2017-11-06 19:42:45'),
(234, 26, 'Radley Pillay', 'rpillay@htmail.com', '', 'This was a full Niagara experience with a bonus.  The tour guide was so knowledgeable and passionate about Canada and the Niagara Falls and kept the excitement levels high.  The additional stops that was made and areas we got to visit was a really great experience in addition to Niagara Falls.  Highly recommend to anyone visiting for the first time, well worth the price and an exceptional, quality experience.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-11-02 16:08:33', 1, '2017-11-02 16:08:33'),
(235, 8, 'Kim F.', 'kfraser@htmail.com', '', 'My mom says it was flipping amazing a must do!!! [Review on Google Plus]', 5, '192.88.135.8', '2017-10-30 13:06:53', 1, '2017-10-30 13:06:53'),
(236, 8, 'Jarlath M', 'jarlathm@htmail.com', '', 'This is the ultimate ,way to View Niagara Falls ,and it surrounding districts, so don\\\'t forget your Camera / phone. this short 10 min flight covers it all ,well organised ,safe operation, will leave you in awe ,as you fly across the mighty Niagara river and falls below you ,Mother Nature in her Element ,an unforgettable memory to take away with you ,well worth the extra expense ,that could well be wasted elsewhere. [As reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-10-28 03:31:25', 1, '2017-10-28 03:31:25'),
(237, 24, 'Zafia Khan', 'zkhan@htmail.com', '', 'Excellent and amazing experience!  Our tour guide and driver Haroon was so funny and informative.  Our group was really great too.  We met some great people and had an amazing time.  Thank you!  Would highly recommend this tour!', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-27 00:17:24', 1, '2017-10-27 00:17:24'),
(238, 27, 'Sacha Rogan', 'srogan@htmail.com', '', 'Perfect!  Tour was well organized.  Loved the lights and the Falls.  Highly recommended.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-23 16:36:33', 1, '2017-10-23 16:36:33'),
(239, 27, 'D. Makowski', 'dmak@htmail.com', '', 'I came for the Winery and that\\\'s what I got!  You have to pay extra for Ice Wine but it was delicious.  The setting was excellent and the wines were high quality. Can\\\'t ask for much more!  The Falls were nice too.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-23 01:25:27', 1, '2017-10-23 01:25:27');
INSERT INTO `tour_reviews` (`ID`, `tour_id`, `name`, `email`, `website`, `description`, `count_star`, `author_IP`, `created_on`, `status`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(240, 26, 'Helen H', 'hhawerchuk@htmail.com', '', 'Niagara Falls was one of the places I wanted to visit in my lifetime and i\\\'m glad that I got to see it.  It didn\\\'t disappoint.  It was great and the boat tour made it larger than loved.  Loved eating over the Falls, this really was a childhood dream and Im glad that I was able to live it out.  The tour was great!  I didn\\\'t know that Niagara Falls has so much to see and do!   I really just thought there was a waterfall!  But there is so much history!  Wine country was amazing I felt like I was in Napa Valley!  The weather was agreeable, the bus was comfortable, I couldn\\\'t ask for anything more.  A perfect day!', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-23 01:20:36', 1, '2017-10-23 01:20:36'),
(241, 18, 'M St. Cartier', 'mstcartier@htmail.com', '', 'I must thank ToNiagara, Niagara Falls is beautiful.  We had a great driver/guide.  I would recommend order the buffet meal because it\\\'s easier than trying to find food everybody will enjoy eating.  Tour was unforgettable.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-23 01:03:42', 1, '2017-10-23 01:03:42'),
(242, 16, 'Donette R', 'donneterwool@gmail.com', '', 'This tour lasted about 6 hours and was absolutely excellent. Good mix of sightseeing, education and fun. Haroon, our tour guide, was relatively new but really, really good. I would recommend this tour to anyone that wants a great half day experience of the Niagara Falls. It was a group tour, so it had a set itinerary and schedule that we all had to stick to. Next time, I would take a private tour so that the tour is tailored to my liking. That said, I highly recommend ToNiagara tours. They are good.', 5, '50.100.44.20', '2017-10-22 12:31:20', 1, '2017-10-22 12:31:20'),
(243, 26, 'Michael R', 'michalrao@gmail.com', '', 'The knowledge of the guide was vast and he held everyone\\\'s interest as we moved to different attractions of the Niagara Falls. I highly recommend ToNiagara!!!', 5, '50.100.44.20', '2017-10-22 12:21:06', 1, '2017-10-22 12:21:06'),
(244, 27, 'Maureen S', 'maureens2017@gail.com', '', 'This tour is a great way to see Niagara Falls. Ilahi is a very knowledgeable guide.The coach bus had 22 passengers, and we were picked up right at the hotel, enabling my husband to enjoy the scenery without having to worry about driving. Included in the tour was a drive to Niagara-On-The-Lake and we also had lunch buffet at Sheraton Fallsview. It is an add-on, but definitely worth the price!', 5, '50.100.44.20', '2017-10-22 12:08:53', 1, '2017-10-22 12:08:53'),
(245, 20, 'faisal uhm', 'faisal@htmail.com', '', 'We came for the Invictus games and didn\\\'t have a lot of time but wanted to see Niagara Falls.  It was easy to book a bus with ToNiagara and travelled to the falls, we had an early flight so we went on the boat and then back home.  It was amazing', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-22 03:45:24', 1, '2017-10-22 03:45:24'),
(246, 4, 'Gabriella Dumpit', 'gdumpit@htmail.com', '', 'Our tour was AMAZING! The tour itself was incredible but our tour guide was also amazing.  So knowledgeable about everything.  I learned so much!  Worth every single penny.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-21 02:43:11', 1, '2017-10-21 02:43:11'),
(247, 17, 'B akruma', 'akruma@htmail.com', '', 'I have to give credit to toniagra I changed our booking information 3 or 4 times but they accommodated me, picked us up and we went to the Falls.  We spent most of our time at the Falls.  At the hornblower they gave us these ponchos to help keep you dry but they were not very effective.  We had a great fun filled day Niagara Fall was a cracking time.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-20 16:41:08', 1, '2017-10-20 16:41:08'),
(248, 25, 'F Yoloko', 'fyoloko@htmail.com', '', 'Took evening tour last week. Weather was great.  This is a wonderful tour, you really get to see a lot of Niagara Falls.  I only wish we could have stayed at the Winery longer.', 5, '70.53.108.131', '2017-10-20 16:29:38', 1, '2017-10-20 16:29:38'),
(249, 24, 'dustin poirier', 'dpoirier@htmail.com', '', 'I was very happy with this tour. Alicia was a great tour guide I was picked up  from my hotel and taken to the Falls.  The Hornblower was a great experience.  Well worth it!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-19 20:18:08', 1, '2017-10-19 20:18:08'),
(250, 18, 'Manny Sanga', 'msanga@htmail.com', '', 'My family is here for a wedding, so we thought we would do something together and take an excursion out to Niagara Falls.  So I reserved a bus from ToNiagara, the driver came on time and took us to 3 wineries, Piliterri Estates, 20 Bees and I can\\\'t remember the other one. We are from British Columbia, the wine there is very similar.  All in all a great day out, the family loved it.  If you are going make sure you take comfortable shoes there is a lot of walking.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 20:39:25', 1, '2017-10-18 20:39:25'),
(251, 20, 'Aaron Biard', 'petfoodtreats@htmail.com', '', 'We took our staff on a Niagara excursion, the bus picked us up and then we went to Timmy\\\'s to grab a quick breakfast.  Once in Niagara Falls we went on the boat cruise and toured NOTL.  Great team building with fun had by all!  Thanks to ToNiagara for accommodating all of us on short notice.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 20:20:17', 1, '2017-10-18 20:20:17'),
(252, 6, 'Reggie Howard', 'rhoward@htmail.com', '', 'I came to Toronto for a conference, the flight left early but I really wanted to see the falls. So I booked this half day tour, which was great.  I went on the boat that takes you upto the falls, ate some lunch, quickly went to the casino and came back.  The driver dropped me off at the airport.  The car was clean and I was picked up on time.  It was a quick great time, well worth it!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 20:08:07', 1, '2017-10-18 20:08:07'),
(253, 25, 'Aila Elouta', 'aelouta@htmail.com', '', 'The fireworks was amazing.  I\\\'ve been to Niagara Falls once in the daytime so I decided to go in the evening.  I was in Oakville and no other bus would pick me up but the ToNiagara guys picked me up and we made it to Niagara Falls.  Did everything, including the boat, helicopter and wine tasting then capped a wonderful evening off with fireworks.  Well worth it! If I coulld give 6 stars I would!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 20:02:32', 1, '2017-10-18 20:02:32'),
(254, 24, 'Susanna Bee', 'susannab@htmail.com', '', 'I took this tour last week, it was great!  Very well run, very well organized.  The Hornblower boat was breathtaking!  I could not recommmend this tour enough.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 19:58:13', 1, '2017-10-18 19:58:13'),
(255, 4, 'Kwame O', 'kwameo@gmail123.com', '', 'Haroon is a well-informed and sociable, he did a wonderful job I loved this tour it was well worth it, I only wish I had gone up in the helicopter.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-18 19:14:53', 1, '2017-10-18 19:14:53'),
(256, 5, 'John Finley', 'johnfin@hot123.com', '', 'You get to see it in the day and at night.  At night it looks amazing with the lights.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-18 14:41:01', 1, '2017-10-18 14:41:01'),
(257, 25, 'Patti Henderson', 'phenderson@htmail.com', '', 'Very embarrassing day :(  Hopped on the wrong bus!!  Wasn\\\'t paying attention and just got on the wrong one!  Luckily customer service emailed/called and texted me!  The bus waited for me and I got onto the ToNiagara one!\r\nFrom there the rest of the trip went smoothly, our group was small so I wasn\\\'t so embarrassed!  Loved the trip and would take it over again and get on the right bus this time!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 04:07:10', 1, '2017-10-18 04:07:10'),
(258, 26, 'Best Mom', 'bestmom@htmail.com', '', 'They are not kidding this is really a full day trip!  I recommend good shoes!  Wine country is amazing I wish we spent more time there though who doesn\\\'t love the Falls.  Haroon was  a great guide and ketp everyone laughing.  Would def recommend', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:57:08', 1, '2017-10-18 03:57:08'),
(259, 24, 'sterling s', 'ssterling@htmail.com', '', 'Here from Australia, loved this trip, we got our seniors discount from ToNiagara and went down to see the falls.  Crossed it off our bucket list and now we are off to another adventure.  Loved it!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:52:24', 1, '2017-10-18 03:52:24'),
(260, 24, 'F Lopez', 'lopez@htmail.com', '', 'It is famous for  a reason!  What a beautiful place!   Everthing in Canada is so clean, it\\\'s great.  Thank you.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:35:36', 1, '2017-10-18 03:35:36'),
(261, 16, 'L Fong', 'fongwww@htmail.com', '', 'Went to the Falls with family went to the Falls then the casino.  Was very fun.  Would recommend, we could only do half day because of early plane flight but glad we came it is worth it to see the Falls', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:32:47', 1, '2017-10-18 03:32:47'),
(262, 14, 'Lacey J', 'ljaxson@htmail.com', '', 'With 4 teens it\\\'s hard to see anything for a long period of time.  We went to Niagara, I chose the half day tour because the kids would get bored, they don\\\'t care for history or wineries.  So we did the Hornblower and had some lunch.  I loved everything about the Falls, i\\\'ll definitely come back and take a private tour and see the rest of the falls.  The tour guide/driver was great we drove in a Yukon SUV which was clean.  Would recommend.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:28:18', 1, '2017-10-18 03:28:18'),
(263, 17, 'Karim Akbar', 'kakbar@htmail.com', '', 'I had a group of 6 we were staying at an Airbnb.  The tour picked us up we went and did the tour and then spent the rest of the time at mini golf and the casino.  It was great fun.  We ate at the buffet which was pretty good', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:22:31', 1, '2017-10-18 03:22:31'),
(264, 27, 'Ang Vantland', 'avantland@htmail.com', '', 'Would recommend this tour, its really beautiful at night, went with my boyfriend for a night out, glad we ate the buffet instead of fast food.  Great way to spend a day out and about.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:17:58', 1, '2017-10-18 03:17:58'),
(265, 26, 'Michael Bagshaw', 'mbagshaw@htmail.com', '', 'Got picked up from my Hotel on Hurontario and went to Niagara Falls.   The Falls were not as large as I imagined but my son absolutely loved the maid of the mist ride.  He got tired from all the walking maybe I should have brought the stroller.  Winery was nice and beautiful scenery.  Great trip!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-10-18 03:14:38', 1, '2017-10-18 03:14:38'),
(266, 15, 'Fletcher C', 'fletcher@dmail.com', '', 'This was a late Valentines day trip, we got a Lincoln Town Car and visited fun places, we stayed overnight and the limo picked us up at the hotel the next day.  It was fun, i\\\'d do it again.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-16 15:58:23', 1, '2017-10-16 15:58:23'),
(267, 4, 'Nabeel B', 'nabeelbawa@yahoo123.com', '', 'It was miserable and raining, but the food was warm and tasty.  Not counting the weather this was a great trip', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-15 22:54:59', 1, '2017-10-15 22:54:59'),
(268, 5, 'Frankie D', 'frankie@gmail123.com', '', 'Tour is well worth the money, me and my gf went on a helicopter and the boat tour.  Arrived back at the hotel late and exhausted!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-14 23:27:28', 1, '2017-10-14 23:27:28'),
(269, 5, 'Hanef', 'hanefd@gmail123.com', '', 'You get to see the Falls twice, once in the afternoon and once in the evening.  The one in the evening is better because there are fireworks.  I went on the boat tour with my kids and we got really wet.  They give you ponchos but you still get wet so be prepared!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-14 23:19:46', 1, '2017-10-14 23:19:46'),
(270, 5, 'Skylar K', 'skylar@dmail.com', '', 'By the end of the tour my wife and I were too tired that we did not go out in Toronto that night.  The tour was enjoyable, we just weren’t expecting it to be that long.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-14 21:48:19', 1, '2017-10-14 21:48:19'),
(271, 5, 'Jack S', 'Jack123@mail.com', '', 'Dinner at the buffet was actually the highlight of the trip for me (there were no fireworks on my trip).  I was very happy with all the selection and the view.  I felt a bit rushed at dinner, probably because I was enjoying the view so much :)', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-14 14:56:59', 1, '2017-10-14 14:56:59'),
(272, 5, 'Hoi F', 'hoif@dmail.com', '', 'I called the customer service to get an explanation of the difference between private tour and bus tour. We had a group of ten (10) people and decided to take the bus because it was cheaper.  The tour was great and everyone had fun, but I wish we had booked a private tour so that we could have spent more time in different areas that interested our group instead.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-12 22:12:45', 1, '2017-10-12 22:12:45'),
(273, 4, 'Jim J', 'jimj@dmail.com', '', 'A group of 8 of us had contemplated taking a private tour but we chose the day tour because it was cheaper.  Tour guide was fun, had some good discussion about the history of the area.  Next time we will do a private tour just so we can go to some different places', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-11 16:58:31', 1, '2017-10-11 16:58:31'),
(274, 5, 'Clarrisa N', 'clarissa@dmail.com', '', 'It was nice to learn about the history of the region from our guide, it made the trip educational and fun.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-11 14:54:21', 1, '2017-10-11 14:54:21'),
(275, 5, 'Jerry Fox', 'jerryme@dmail.com', '', 'If I wasn\\\'t so afraid I would have went on the helicopter tour, I wish I had done that but seeing the Falls was great!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-11 14:38:00', 1, '2017-10-11 14:38:00'),
(276, 15, 'Nancy D', 'nancyd@fmail.com', '', 'Went for a girls night out to the casino!  Short trip the custom trip was the easiest way to get all of us picked up and dropped of safely.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-10 16:01:16', 1, '2017-10-10 16:01:16'),
(277, 4, 'Martha K', 'marthak@fmail.com', '', 'Absolutely amazing tour. Our guide was highly professional and friendly. He was full of information about the Falls and other attraction. There is no better way to see the Falls and understand is sheer size and beauty than from the air chopper ride!!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-09 22:23:19', 1, '2017-10-09 22:23:19'),
(278, 8, 'David R.', 'davidr@htmail.com', '', 'First come, first serve. Best prices are found online in advance. Got there at 9:30a, couple of buses in front of us... ugh. Half hour wait, not too bad. Decent gift shop. 12 minute flight, smooth, didn\\\'t make us queasy. Workers take a few photos for you to look at on way out. We got the high res JPG on a thumb drive for $30, it was very detailed and appropriate for large poster sized prints if desired. Need to do this if debating. [As reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-10-09 06:12:18', 1, '2017-10-09 06:12:18'),
(279, 7, 'Malcom S', 'malcom@dmail.com', '', 'Me and 4 friends wanted to visit Niagara in style so we rented a Limo and went to the Casino and a few night clubs and then home.  Driver was on time, the limo was clean, it was a great night.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-07 15:46:42', 1, '2017-10-07 15:46:42'),
(280, 5, 'Victor E', 'vickie@gmail123.com', '', 'I thought the Tour would be kind of boring but there is lots to do and see.  The flower clock was a good stop for pictures and the Falls was also a good place to take pictures expecially at night.  This was a great tour i\\\'m glad I went.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-06 23:32:26', 1, '2017-10-06 23:32:26'),
(281, 8, 'Becky F.', 'beckyf@htmail.com', '', 'Helicopter over Niagara Falls, do I need to say anymore? Just wow. \r\nIf you are planning a trip to see the falls you need to do it via helicopter. You get a whole different experience that just standing looking at the falls doesn’t give you. \r\nFabulous experience and well worth the money.[As reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-10-06 03:34:48', 1, '2017-10-06 03:34:48'),
(282, 5, 'Desiree C', 'desiree@fmailcom.com', '', 'I went on the trip in the evening with my family because I didn\\\'t want large crowd and I wanted cooler weather.  There were still a lot of people at the Falls (which is to be expected) but my kids really enjoyed the fireworks at night.  That was very fun', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-05 23:36:33', 1, '2017-10-05 23:36:33'),
(283, 4, 'Jack B', 'jackb@fmail.com', '', 'The buses are clean and well maintained! Great tour guide too ! Would recommend!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-05 21:33:46', 1, '2017-10-05 21:33:46'),
(284, 4, 'Horace M', 'horacem@fmail.com', '', 'Lots to do on the trip and so many key places of tourist attraction covered. Enjoyed thoroughly!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-05 19:07:37', 1, '2017-10-05 19:07:37'),
(285, 5, 'Hideo N', 'hideon@fmail.com', '', 'Very much appreciated a good trip overall !', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-10-04 21:21:35', 1, '2017-10-04 21:21:35'),
(286, 4, 'David Kluivert', 'bearhugs@gmail.com1', '', 'Words can\\\'t really describe it!  It was wonderful thank you To niagara!', 5, '64.229.3.74', '2017-10-04 01:32:15', 1, '2017-10-04 01:32:15'),
(287, 4, 'Layla B', 'laylalala@gmail123.com', '', 'You will not regret taking this tour it has something for everyone, but when you get back to the hotel you will be tired!  You have to pay extra for the lunch, it\\\'s buffet style and the view is wonderful', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-30 23:02:03', 1, '2017-09-30 23:02:03'),
(288, 5, 'toniagara', 'admin@woolance.com', '', 'Loved it!  Thank you ToNiagara the tour was aces!!!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-30 17:27:20', 1, '2017-09-30 17:27:20'),
(289, 4, 'Sidrah Chakh', 'awesomegirls@gmail.com1', '', 'I went on a Toronto to Niagara Falls Bus trip with ToNiagara and stayed overnight at Nigara on the lake.  They picked us up tomorrow morning and we went back to Toronto it was perfect', 5, '64.229.3.74', '2017-09-30 00:08:19', 1, '2017-09-30 00:08:19'),
(290, 4, 'S Stevenson', 'stevenson@htmail.com', '', 'Our 1st time to Niagara .We thoroughly enjoyed the whole outing with our tour guide Alicia .( hope my spelling is correct ) .she had a nice clear voice ,and at times very humorous . I would highly recommend your tour ,it was a well organized memorable day.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-09-29 01:22:00', 1, '2017-09-29 01:22:00'),
(291, 5, 'Vanessa V', 'vanessam@tmail.com', '', 'I wore open toed shoes which was a bad idea, the fireworks made up for it!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 20:44:16', 1, '2017-09-28 20:44:16'),
(292, 5, 'Dinesh R', 'dineshr@dmail.com', '', 'To Niagara did this right, the tour was informative and well organized, we got to see everything though some parts of the trip seemed rushed.  It\\\'s the best you can ask for from a tour.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 20:39:27', 1, '2017-09-28 20:39:27'),
(293, 5, 'Ganesh R', 'ganeshr@fmail.com', '', 'Loved the fireworks, loved the moonlight, we went on this tour as a romantic getaway and it was such a good idea.  We\\\'ll have to do it again but take a custom tour so we can eat at a gourmet restaurant.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 20:37:05', 1, '2017-09-28 20:37:05'),
(294, 5, 'Lacey J', 'laceyj@dmail.com', '', 'I went at night and it was cooler because of the mist so take a jacket if you go on a night tour!  But the falls were BEAUTIFUL, they light them up then the fireworks topped it off.  I\\\'m glad I bought dinner because the tour is long and you get hungry', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 20:35:11', 1, '2017-09-28 20:35:11'),
(295, 19, 'Carlos E', 'carlose@gmail1q23.com', '', 'A private tour is good, just bring your wallet because nothing is prepaid, any attractions you have to pay for yourself.  I went on a helicopter trip, boat ride and had a nice lunch, which was a little costly but still worth it!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 16:06:47', 1, '2017-09-28 16:06:47'),
(296, 4, 'Brian Mohr', 'bmohr@htmail.com', '', 'Great trip, no stress and very informative!  Totally enjoyed our day.  Thanks.', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-09-28 13:09:04', 1, '2017-09-28 13:09:04'),
(297, 4, 'Kevin P', 'kevinp@dmail.com', '', 'Came to Ontario for a short visit and had booked this trip! Still cant get over the beauty of the Falls !', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-28 00:12:54', 1, '2017-09-28 00:12:54'),
(298, 4, 'Mel S', 'mels@gmail123.com', '', 'Good tour, bus arrived on time, basically stuck to the schedule, not a huge fan of the smallest chapel in the world, but it was cute.  A good day was had by all.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-27 22:29:52', 1, '2017-09-27 22:29:52'),
(299, 5, 'Louise M', 'louised@fmail.com', '', 'ToNiagara does a great job..Very professional and very thorough. Thank you ToNiagara!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-27 19:36:22', 1, '2017-09-27 19:36:22'),
(300, 4, 'Charley P', 'charleyp@fmail.com', '', 'This is a great trip to make if you are planning to go with a significant other. Went with my boyfriend . Took lots of pics and covered a lot in this 10 hour trip. It ran on schedule too which was great ! Would recommend!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-27 19:30:57', 1, '2017-09-27 19:30:57'),
(301, 5, 'Wilbur S', 'wilbursmith@fmail.com', '', 'Having outlets on the bus was great to keep the kids entertained!  We all had a fun time would definitely recommend.', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-27 14:46:42', 1, '2017-09-27 14:46:42'),
(302, 8, 'Richard H.', 'richardh@htmail.com', '', 'Had a great day and a brilliant experience. Flight over the falls was approx 10-12 minutes. All was well organised and queues were dealt with swiftly. Plenty of parking. Would thoroughly recommend. Thanks to all concerned. [As Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-09-27 03:36:57', 1, '2017-09-27 03:36:57'),
(303, 4, 'Lisa Dunstan', 'lisad@den.com', '', 'This was the best day ever!!!!  Bus picked us up, the tour groups was not large, we got to see the Niagara Falls and surrounding area.  It was perfect!  Memories forever!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-26 23:08:54', 1, '2017-09-26 23:08:54'),
(304, 5, 'Kwako B', 'kwakob@gmail.com', '', 'Harry was well-informed, interesting, and sociable. He did a magnificent job. Fabulous and outstanding. this was a well put together tour make sure to stop for ice cream!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-25 21:16:46', 1, '2017-09-25 21:16:46'),
(305, 5, 'Laticia D', 'laticia@prison.com', '', 'It was a long tour!  But the lights and the fireworks made it all worth it!  Thank you', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-25 14:35:19', 1, '2017-09-25 14:35:19'),
(306, 8, 'Lindan 498', 'lindan@htmail.com', '', 'Fantastic tour - prompt, courteous &amp; smooth ride. The view from above is something else -- I would do this again in a heartbeat. [As Reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-09-25 04:07:12', 1, '2017-09-25 04:07:12'),
(307, 8, 'T. H.', 'tienyho@htmail.com', '', 'I went there with my husband and daughter to celebrate our 10th Anniversary trip. The trip takes about 10 mins but has to line up about 30 mins for the ride but it worth.[As reviewed on TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-09-25 03:38:42', 1, '2017-09-25 03:38:42'),
(308, 4, 'Danilo Gonzalez', 'dgonzalez@htmail.com', '', 'Awesome Trip! Crew was very nice and helpful and the whole experience very well planed.  From the start at the whirlpool to the end at the vineyard everything was carefully explained and programmed.  There was time to wander around Niagara shop for souvenirs and even they gave us a mug as a gift from the travel.  I surely would recommend anyone to give this tour a try!', 5, '70.53.109.6', '2017-09-24 17:07:11', 1, '2017-09-24 17:07:11'),
(309, 8, 'Rita E.', 'ritae@htmail.com', '', 'What a ride , just 10 minutes but worth IT . We had a great time , great pilot . The waiting time was little because we were there early , i recomend IT . Dont be late . \r\nThis is a must .\r\nRita E.\r\nBergen , Norway [Reviewed from TripAdvisor]', 5, '70.54.45.156', '2017-09-24 03:43:40', 1, '2017-09-24 03:43:40'),
