(319, 4, 'Jeremiah B', 'jeremiahb@fmail.com', '', 'My girlfriend and I took the Niagara Falls day tour with a pick up from Starbucks in Toronto.  Booked it online, pick up was smooth, got to Niagara Falls around 11 a.m. and hopped on the Hornblower boat tour.  I’m glad they provided us with ponchos, because the spray from the Falls was a lot!  We had a few minutes after the boat tour to explore but we didn’t go to far.  Next was the buffet at the Sheraton Fallsview Hotel, the scenery was fantastic and the food was great.  We went to the Floral Clock to see what my girlfriend called a ‘a blizzard of colors’.  To me it was just pretty colors on a clock.  Then to the main attraction (for me at least) the wine taste.  You better believe I tasted every type of wine they offered me, even tried the grape juice.  My girlfriend wouldn’t let me buy any of the ice wine which I was told is great on ice cream, but by that time I was too tired to argue with her.  We carted ourselves back on the bus and took a slow, satisfied ride back to our hotels.  It was an amazing day!', 5, '174.91.76.222', '2017-09-20 22:27:17', 1, '2017-09-20 22:27:17'),
