(25, 'Niagara Falls', 'Family Tours,History & Culture,Sightseeing tours', 'Canada', 'Oakville To Niagara Falls Evening Tour', 'oakville-to-niagara-falls-evening-tour', ' ', 'Oakville to Niagara Falls Evening Tour | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Oakville to Niagara Falls Evening Tour | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Free pickup/dropoff from Oakville. 9.5-hour tour. Affordable, visit all the major attractions. See the evening Niagara Fall Illumination & Fireworks (seasonal).', '<h3 class=\"heading3\"><p>Treat Yourself To An Amazing Light Show In Niagara Falls Every Evening â€“ Tour Available on Friday &amp; Sunday Only</p>\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n          <p>In the evening the Niagara Falls are lit up in spectacular colours throughout the year.  In the summer months at 10PM a dazzling fireworks display is held over the Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p>On our ToNiagara Evening Tour from Oakville to Niagara Falls you will board the Hornblower Boat Cruise where you will get up close and personal with the Niagara Falls.  The Hornblower Boat Cruise (formerly known as the Maid of the Mist) is perhaps the most popular attraction because people love to witness the power of the Falls up close (you are provided rain pochos to keep you dry).  ToNiagara passengers are given VIP access to the Hornblower boat and can skip any long lineup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then travel back in time to the picturesque town of Niagara-on-the-Lake. This Victorian era town still retains much of its 19th century architecture.  You will learn about the history of Niagara-on-the-Lake and visit some historical monuments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No Oakville to Niagara Falls Tour is complete without visiting one of the regions many wineries, where you will get a behind the scenes look at how grapes are grown, crushed and pressed to produce some of the world\'s finest wines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dinner is then served (for those who ordered the Dinner Buffet Add On), you will be escorted to the Sheraton Fallsview Restaurant where you will be treated  to a mouthwatering meal with a stunning view overlooking the Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally (in the summer and fall) you will witness a dazzling fireworks display over the Niagara Falls before you are dropped off back in Oakville.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n          </div>', 'Niagara Falls', '9.5 Hours', '5', '', '', 'CA', 'Price', 199, ' ', '', 'Seniors (Age 60+)', 189, ' ', 'Children (4-12 years)', 139, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', '', '', '', '<ul class=\"inclu_list\">\r\n                       <li>Hotel pickup and drop-off </li>\r\n            <li>Wine Tasting At A Local Winery </li>\r\n            <li>Niagara-On-The-Lake Tour </li>\r\n            <li>Tour Guide </li>\r\n            <li>Unlimited Free Bottled Water </li>\r\n            <li>Wheelchair Access On Request* </li>\r\n            <li>Free Lanyards</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n          ', '<ul class=\"addon_list\">\r\n                       <li>Helicopter Ride (Add On)</li>\r\n 			<li>Buffet Lunch or Dinner (Add On) </li>\r\n            <li>Airport Drop-Off (Add On) </li>\r\n			<li>Next Day Pick Up (Add On) </li>\r\n            <li>Hornblower Cruise (seasonal) </li>\r\n          </ul>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>We pickup and drop-off from most hotels in Toronto, Airport area hotels and Mississauga Hotels*</p>\r\n<p>You will be requested to enter the pickup location in the last step of online booking. Your pick up time will be mentioned in the booking confirmation.</p>\r\n                  \r\n                  </div>', '<p>If a Day or Evening Bus Tour is cancelled less than 24 hours ahead&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>&nbsp;will be provided.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n\r\n<li>You are responsible for arriving on time to your Niagara Falls Bus Tour. The pickup vehicle will usually wait for a few minutes; however, if you arrive late and miss the tour, NO REFUND will be provided. ToNiagara will specify your pickup time and location through email.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>If, for any reason your tour is cancelled (due to inclement weather or other unforeseen circumstances), you will be notified as soon as possible and receive a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">FULL REFUND</span>&nbsp;to your credit card or any other method of payment as applicable.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Rescheduling your tour to another date is free of charge.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>To switch your tour from day tour to evening tour, custom tour or vice versa, you will have to pay the difference in the tour fee. There are no additional processing fees. If you are switching to a less expensive tour, ToNiagara will refund the difference to your credit card.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>In the rare event of a bus/vehicle breakdown all efforts will be made to continue the tour (another vehicle or vehicles may be sent to pick you up.)&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>&nbsp;will be provided for any time lost on the tour or change in passenger vehicle. If the tour is cancelled due to bus/vehicle breakdown ToNiagara will be provide a full refund.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '', '20180821095538_755.jpg', '20180821095538_376.jpg', '', 'asd', 5, 1, 17, 22, '2018-08-21 09:55:38'),
(26, 'Niagara Falls', 'Family Tours,History & Culture,Sightseeing tours', 'Canada', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Day Tour', 'mississauga-to-niagara-falls-day-tour', ' ', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Day Tour | Book Online â€“ Niagara Falls Tour', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Day Tour', 'Free pickup/dropoff. 9.5-hour guided Mississauga To Niagara Falls Day Tour. Hornblower Niagara Cruise, Whirlpool Rapids, Floral Clock, Niagara-on-the-Lake & many more stops!', '<h3 class=\"heading3\"><p>Take a ToNiagara Day Tour From Mississauga To Niagara Falls And See One Of  The Wonders Of The World!</p>\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n          <p>Niagara Falls is a magical place with lots to see and even more to do.  Take a ToNiagara Day Tour from Mississauga to Niagara Falls where you will embark on an adventurous day visiting one of the most famous landmarks in the world today.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p>We first drive down to Niagara Falls, which takes approximately 90 minutes.  When you reach the Falls you will board the Hornblower Boat Cruise (formerly Maid of the Mist).  The Hornblower Boat Cruise is probably the most popular attraction in Niagara Falls, the boat takes you past the American and Bridal Veil Falls and right up to the base of the massive Horseshoe Falls for a thrilling show of Nature\'s awesome power (ponchos are provided to keep you dry).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ToNiagara has obtained VIP access for our passengers which allow you to skip any long lineups when boarding the Hornblower boat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those who order the Lunch Buffet Add On, you will be taken to the Penthouse Level of the the Sheraton Fallsview Restaurant where you will be treated to a sumptuous meal with a stunning view overlooking the Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then its time  to learn about some history, we travel to the quaint town of Niagara-on-the-Lake and learn about the War of 1812 and view the amazing Victorian architecture of this 19th century town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Niagara Region is also famous for its many wineries.  On our ToNiagara Mississauga to Niagara Falls Day Tour you will get a behind the scenes look at how grapes are grown, crushed and pressed to produce some of the world\'s finest wines.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n          </div>', 'Niagara Falls', '9.5 Hours', '12', '', '', 'CA', 'Price', 149, ' ', '', 'Seniors (Age 60+)', 139, ' ', 'Children (4-12 years)', 119, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', '', '', '', '<ul class=\"inclu_list\">\r\n            <li>Hornblower Cruise (seasonal) </li>\r\n            <li>Hotel pickup and drop-off </li>\r\n            <li>Wine Tasting At A Local Winery </li>\r\n            <li>Niagara-On-The-Lake Tour </li>\r\n            <li>Tour Guide </li>\r\n            <li>Unlimited Free Bottled Water </li>\r\n            <li>Wheelchair Access On Request* </li>\r\n            <li>Free Lanyards</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n          \r\n          ', '<ul class=\"addon_list\">\r\n                       <li>Helicopter Ride (Add On)</li>\r\n 			<li>Buffet Lunch or Dinner (Add On) </li>\r\n            <li>Airport Drop-Off (Add On) </li>\r\n			<li>Next Day Pick Up (Add On) </li>\r\n                      </ul>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>We pickup and drop-off from most hotels in Toronto, Airport area hotels and Mississauga Hotels*</p>\r\n<p>You will be requested to enter the pickup location in the last step of online booking. Your pick up time will be mentioned in the booking confirmation.</p>\r\n                  \r\n                  </div>', '<p>If a Day or Evening Bus Tour is cancelled less than 24 hours ahead&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>&nbsp;will be provided.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n<li>You are responsible for arriving on time to your Niagara Falls Bus Tour. The pickup vehicle will usually wait for a few minutes; however, if you arrive late and miss the tour, NO REFUND will be provided. ToNiagara will specify your pickup time and location through email.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>If, for any reason your tour is cancelled (due to inclement weather or other unforeseen circumstances), you will be notified as soon as possible and receive a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">FULL REFUND</span>&nbsp;to your credit card or any other method of payment as applicable.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Rescheduling your tour to another date is free of charge.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>To switch your tour from day tour to evening tour, custom tour or vice versa, you will have to pay the difference in the tour fee. There are no additional processing fees. If you are switching to a less expensive tour, ToNiagara will refund the difference to your credit card.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>In the rare event of a bus/vehicle breakdown all efforts will be made to continue the tour (another vehicle or vehicles may be sent to pick you up.)&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>&nbsp;will be provided for any time lost on the tour or change in passenger vehicle. If the tour is cancelled due to bus/vehicle breakdown ToNiagara will be provide a full refund.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '', '20180821101437_604.jpg', '20180821101437_141.jpg', '', 'asd', 5, 1, 13, 23, '2018-08-21 10:14:37'),
(27, 'Niagara Falls', 'Family Tours,History & Culture,Sightseeing tours', 'Canada', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Evening Tour', 'mississauga-to-niagara-falls-evening-tour', ' ', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Evening Tour | Book Online â€“ Niagara Falls Tour', 'Mississauga To Niagara Falls Evening Tour', 'View Niagara Falls by day and night on this 9.5-hour Mississauga To Niagara Falls Evening Tour. FREE Hornblower Niagara Boat Cruise. Visit lots of places. Browse for more details!', '<h3 class=\"heading3\"><p>The Falls Provide An Amazing Light Show At Night â€“ Tour Available on Friday &amp; Sunday Only</p>\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n          <p>Niagara Falls comes alive in the evening. The Falls are illuminated in exciting colours and throughout the summer months fireworks provide another reason to see the Falls in the evening (Fireworks Monday through Friday at 10PM from June 12 through September 4. Additional displays on May 19, 21, 22, 26, 28, and 29, July 1 and 2, and September 3). The night time truly is the right time when visiting the Falls! Please note Niagara Falls evening tours are available only on Friday &amp; Sunday.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p> Our Mississauga to Niagara Falls Evening Tour will take you from Mississauga to the Niagara Falls where you will board the Hornblower Boat and be shuttled to the base of the Great Horseshoe Falls (the largest of the Niagara Falls), it is a truly unique photography opportunity and fun for the entire family.  We then travel back in time to the picturesque town of Niagara-on-the-Lake. This quaint town still retains its 19th century charm from the Victorian era as well as it\'s stunning architecture.  No Mississauga to Niagara Falls Tour is complete without visiting one of the regions many wineries, where you will get a behind the scenes look at how grapes are grown, crushed and pressed to produce some of the world\'s finest wines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those who order the Dinner Buffet Add O