 for a few minutes; however, if you arrive late and miss the tour, NO REFUND will be provided. ToNiagara will specify your pickup time and location through email.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>If, for any reason your tour is cancelled (due to inclement weather or other unforeseen circumstances), you will be notified as soon as possible and receive a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">FULL REFUND</span>&nbsp;to your credit card or any other method of payment as applicable.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Rescheduling your tour to another date is free of charge.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>To switch your tour from day tour to evening tour, custom tour or vice versa, you will have to pay the difference in the tour fee. There are no additional processing fees. If you are switching to a less expensive tour, ToNiagara will refund the difference to your credit card.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>In the rare event of a bus/vehicle breakdown all efforts will be made to continue the tour (another vehicle or vehicles may be sent to pick you up.)&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>&nbsp;will be provided for any time lost on the tour or change in passenger vehicle. If the tour is cancelled due to bus/vehicle breakdown ToNiagara will be provide a full refund.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '', '20180821102321_822.jpg', '20180821102321_781.jpg', '', 'asd', 5, 1, 10, 24, '2018-08-21 10:23:21'),
(28, 'Niagara Falls', 'Family Tours', 'USA', 'Niagara Falls Tour: Half-Day Charter Fishing Adventures Niagara Falls, New York', 'toniagara-half-day-charter-fishing-adventures-niagara-falls-new-york', 'Half Day Trip (6 Hours)', 'Half Day Charter Fishing â€“ Niagara Falls NY | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Half Day Charter Fishing â€“ Niagara Falls NY | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Go on a morning or afternoon fishing expedition on the Niagara River. You must have a fishing license. Enjoy the beautiful scenery, catch trout, sardines!', '<h3 class=\"heading3\"><p>Half-Day Charter Fishing on the Niagara River (U.S.A side)</p></h3>\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n<p>If you are interested in fishing, this guided fishing trip is for you! Whether you are an experienced angler or you have never held a fishing pole we cater to people of all experience levels.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p>Join us for an excursion to the Niagara River, our boats are equipped with state-of-the-art electronics and comfort items to make the time you spend on the water a memorable once-in-a-lifetime experience.</p>\r\n<p>Spend a half-day with us and experience an entire new way to the discover the Niagara River.</p>\r\n<p>Whether fishing in the spring, when the river begins to swell, summer when the fish are on the move or in the fall among the changing leaves, anytime is a great time to fish!</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"include_wra\">\r\n            <div class=\"row\">\r\n        	  <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n              <h2><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> What is Included?</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <ul class=\"inclu_list2\">\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Boat (seats a maximum of 3 adults)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n				<li>Fishing gear (rod reel, line leaders, flies/lures/bait)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Safety equipment (life vests)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Snacks (potato chips and water)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n              \r\n              </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n              <h2><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> What you must bring?</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <ul class=\"inclu_list2\">\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Fishing license (current NY, PA or Ontario fishing license)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Be dressed adequately for the weather</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Camera</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Sunglasses/sunscreen</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Bug spray</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Some customers prefer to bring their own snacks/beverages</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Waders (only necessary if you will be walking and wading through water in Spring/Fall or Winter)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n     		</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Niagara Falls', '6AM to 12PM or 1PM to 7PM (weather permitting)', '0', '', '', 'US', 'Price', 350, ' ', '', ' ', 0, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>A full refund issued by ToNiagara if  your tour is cancelled at least 48 hours before scheduled tour departure (this includes any issue arising at the U.S.A/Canada Border.  <strong>NO REFUND</strong> will be issued if the tour is cancelled less than 48 hours before scheduled tour departure time.</p>                  \r\n                  </div>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <strong>Where do you meet customers who are taking the Chartered Fishing Trip?</strong>\r\n<p>It depends on what we\'re fishing for and time of year.  Most of the time it will be either in Lewiston or Buffalo.  The day prior, I send a map link to the client and call them to make sure they know how to get there.  </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of snacks will be onboard?</strong>\r\n<p>Breakfast is prepared before departure (bacon, egg, hashbrown, and cheese burrito).  On the boat there will be potato chips and water on the boat as well. </p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<strong>Are alcholic beverages allowed on the boat?</strong>\r\n<p>Clients can bring their own beverages (within reason)</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>What happens if the weather is bad?</strong>\r\n<p>Tours can be rescheduled or else a refund will provided</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>How early should I book this trip?</strong>\r\n<p>All booking must be made at least 8 days prior.  If you must go before that please call support.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to bring anything?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, Fishing license is mandatory be dressed appropriately for the weather.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of boat will you use?</strong>\r\n<p>Ranger 1885 Deep V â€“ it seats max 3 customers. </p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<strong>Is there any age restrictions?</strong>\r\n<p>Any individuals under 18 must be accompanied by an adult or have parental permission. </p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<strong>Do you give a little safety orientation first?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, there will be a 15 minute safety orientation before going on the trip</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Apart from the fishing gear what else do you bring?</strong>\r\n<p>all fishing gear, tackle, safety equipment, snacks, water and a sense of humor!</p>\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n     \r\n                  </div>', '', '20180821110527_356.jpg', '20180821110527_592.jpg', '', '236096', 5, 1, 36, 25, '2018-08-21 11:05:27'),
(29, 'Niagara Falls', 'Family Tours', 'USA', 'Niagara Falls Tour: Full Day Charter Fishing Adventure â€“ Niagara Falls, New York', 'toniagara-full-day-charter-fishing-adventure-niagara-falls-new-york', 'Full Day Trip (12 Hours)', 'Full Day Charter Fishing Adventure â€“ Niagara Falls USA | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Full Day Charter Fishing Adventure â€“ Niagara Falls USA | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Experience the outdoors with a fishing trip on the Niagara River. Boats start from Lewiston or Buffalo, NY. Be one with nature 6 am to 6 pm. Customer must have a fishing license.', '<h3 class=\"heading3\"><p>Charter Fishing on the Niagara River (U.S.A side)</p></h3>\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n<p>If you are interested in fishing, this guided fishing trip is for you! Whether you are an experienced angler or you have never held a fishing pole we cater to people of all experience levels.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p>Join us for an excursion to the Niagara River, our boats are equipped with state-of-the-art electronics and comfort items to make the time you spend on the water a memorable once-in-a-lifetime experience.</p>\r\n<p>Spend a full day with us and experience an entire new way to the discover the Niagara River.</p>\r\n<p>On a full day excursion we can fully explore the river, work numerous drifts and chalk up multiple species.</p>\r\n<div class=\"include_wra\">\r\n            <div class=\"row\">\r\n        	  <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n              <h2><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> What is Included?</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <ul class=\"inclu_list2\">\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Boat (seats a maximum of 3 adults)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Fishing gear (rod reel, line leaders, flies/lures/bait)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Safety equipment (life vests)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <li>Snacks (potato chips and water)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n              \r\n              </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <div class=\"col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n              <h2><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> What you must bring?</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n              <ul class=\"inclu_list2\">\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li> Fishing license (current NY, PA or Ontario fishing license)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Be dressed adequately for the weather</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Camera</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Sunglasses/sunscreen</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Bug spray</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Some customers prefer to bring their own snacks/beverages</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                 <li>Waders (only necessary if you will be walking and wading through water in Spring/Fall or Winter)</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n              </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n     		</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n          </div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Niagara Falls', '6AM to 6PM', '0', '', '', 'US', 'Price', 450, ' ', '', ' ', 0, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>A full refund issued by ToNiagara if  your tour is cancelled at least 48 hours before scheduled tour departure (this includes any issue arising at the U.S.A/Canada Border.  <strong>NO REFUND</strong> will be issued if the tour is cancelled less than 48 hours before scheduled tour departure time.</p>                  \r\n                  </div>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <strong>Where do you meet customers who are taking the Chartered Fishing Trip?</strong>\r\n<p>It depends on what we\'re fishing for and time of year.  Most of the time it will be either in Lewiston or Buffalo.  The day prior, I send a map link to the client and call them to make sure they know how to get there. </p>\r\n \r\n<strong>What kind of snacks will be onboard?</strong>\r\n<p>Breakfast is prepared before departure (bacon, egg, hashbrown, and cheese burrito).  On the boat there will be potato chips and water on the boat as well. </p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<strong>Are alcholic beverages allowed on the boat?</strong>\r\n<p>Clients can bring their own beverages (within reason)</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>What happens if the weather is bad?</strong>\r\n<p>Tours can be rescheduled or else a refund will provided</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>How early should I book this trip?</strong>\r\n<p>All booking must be made at least 8 days prior.  If you must go before that please call support.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to bring anything?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, Fishing license is mandatory be dressed appropriately for the weather.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of boat will you use?</strong>\r\n<p>Ranger 1885 Deep V â€“ it seats max 3 customers.  </p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there any age restrictions?</strong>\r\n<p>Any individuals under 18 must be accompanied by an adult or have parental permission. </p>\r\n \r\n<strong>Do you give a little safety orientation first?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, there will be a 15 minute safety orientation before going on the trip</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Apart from the fishing gear what else do you bring?</strong>\r\n<p>all fishing gear, tackle, safety equipment, snacks, water and a sense of humor! </p>\r\n</div>      \r\n                  </div>', '', '20180821111418_344.jpg', '20180821111418_276.jpg', '', '236068', 5, 1, 48, 26, '2018-08-21 11:14:18'),
(30, 'Niagara Falls,Niagara Falls Boat Tours', 'Sightseeing tours', 'USA', 'Maid in America Tour Niagara Falls, New York', 'maid-in-america-tour-niagara-falls-new-york', 'Half Day Trip (4 Hours)', 'Maid Of The Mist Tour â€“ Niagara Falls, NY | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Maid Of The Mist Tour â€“ Niagara Falls, NY | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Visit Niagara Falls State Park USA. 4-hour tour includes Maid of the Mist boat tour. Visit Goat Island, power plant and other sights on the US side of Niagara Falls.', '<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n<p>Discover the American side of Niagara Falls (Niagara Falls, NY) on this amazing Maid in America Tour. </p>\r\n<p>This 4 hour tour will take you to all the popular attractions on the American side of the Falls including:</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Horseshoe Falls</li>\r\n<li>American Falls</li>\r\n<li>Bridal Veil Falls</li>\r\n<li>Upper Niagara River and Rapids</li>\r\n<li>Whirlpool and Gorge</li>\r\n<li>Maid of the Mist Boat Ride</li>\r\n<li>Panoramic view from the NYS Observation Tower</li>\r\n<li>Power Plants, Control Dams and Water Intakes</li>\r\n<li>Cave of the Winds Trip</li>\r\n<li>Goat Island, Luna Island, Three Sisters Islands</li>\r\n<li>History and stories of the Niagara Region</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Niagara Falls', '4 Hours', '0', '', '', 'US', 'Price', 104.95, ' ', '', ' ', 0, ' ', 'Children (5-12 years)', 78.71, ' ', 'Infants (0-4 years)', 0, ' Free', '', '', '', '<ul class=\"inclu_list\">\r\n<li>Admission onto the Observation Tower</li>\r\n<li>Maid of the Mist Boat Cruise</li>\r\n<li>Cave of the Winds, exploration at the bottom of the Falls</li>\r\n<li>Guided tour of the Niagara Region with a fully licensed guide/driver</li>\r\n<li>Complimentary Pickup from most downtown Niagara Falls USA hotels</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '<p>Complimentary Pickup from most downtown Niagara Falls USA hotels (you must contact the number provided on your ticket at least 24 hours before your tour and provide your pickup destination).</p>\r\n<p>You must present a printed copy of your electronic voucher to your guide at time of boarding&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Border crossing documents such as Passport and/or Visa required for cross-border tours</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Departure Times:</h2>\r\n<p><strong>CANADIAN DEPARTURES (most Niagara Falls Hotels):</strong> 9AM (TOUR START TIME)</p>\r\n<p><strong>AMERICAN DEPARTURES:</strong> 9AM, 11AM, 1PM, 3PM(TOUR START TIME)</p>\r\n<p><strong>BUFFALO DEPARTURES:</strong> 11AM(TOUR START TIME)</p>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>A full refund issued by ToNiagara if your tour is cancelled at least 48 hours before scheduled tour departure (this includes any issue arising at the U.S.A/Canada Border. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND </span>will be issued if the tour is cancelled less than 48 hours before scheduled tour departure time.</p>\r\n                  \r\n                  </div>', '<strong>What type of documentation do I need for crossing the border on my tour?</strong>\r\n<p>United States and Canadian citizens ages 16 and older must present one of the following travel documents at the border:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n\r\n<li>Valid U.S. or Canadian Passport</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Enhanced Driver\'s License (EDL)</li>\r\n\r\n<li>U.S. Passport Card</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Trusted Traveler Program Card</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<p>United States and Canadian citizens under the age of 16, or under the age of 19 traveling with a school, religious or other youth group, must present one of the following travel documents at the border:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n\r\n<li>Original or certified copy of birth certificate</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Naturalization Certificate</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Consular report of birth abroad</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Canadian Citizenship Card</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Lawful Permanent Residents of the United States must present a Permanent Resident Card (\"Green Card\", INS Form I-1551) at the border.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Residents of nations other than the United States and Canada may require a Canadian Visa along with their passport to enter Canada. Contact your national consulate before leaving home. International visitors will require passports to cross the border. Citizens of some countries may require a Canadian Visa as well. Be sure to check with our staff when booking your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>For the most up-to-date border crossing information, please access the following website: www.cbp.gov (Subject to Change)</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does my tour depart from?</strong>\r\n<p>There are multiple pickup points on both sides of the border, all within walking or driving distance from most hotels. We will provide directions to your departure point when you confirm  your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to wait until I arrive at Niagara Falls to book my tour?</strong>\r\n<p>Due to the popularity of our tours, we recommend that you reserve your seats as soon as possible to guard against the possibility of a sell-out.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>What type of clothing is recommended for the tour?</strong>\r\n<p>Comfortable walking shoes or sneakers are recommended. It is always a few degrees cooler near the water, so a jacket or sweater is also a good idea for cooler temperatures.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to bring money on tour with me?</strong>\r\n<p>The price of your tour includes all attraction and parking fees. You may want to bring some spending money or a credit card with you as you will be given the opportunity to purchase snacks or souvenirs. Tipping your tour guide is at your discretion.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you pickup from Buffalo?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, we pick-up from any downtown or airport hotel in Buffalo for our tours.  There is an additional $40 round trip fee per party for these pickups, you can discuss when you confirm your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Are meals included?</strong>\r\n<p>No, meals are not provided.  Breaks will be given throughout the tour in order for guests to purchase something to eat on their own.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n\r\n<li>You must present a printed copy of your electronic voucher to your guide at time of boarding </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Cameras and camcorders are welcome and encouraged!</li>\r\n \r\n<li>Comfortable clothing and shoes recommended </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Collapsible wheelchairs permitted with 48 hour advance notice </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Passengers must confirm Hotel AND select pickup time at least 48 hours prior to tour </li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Other information</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>You must present a printed copy of your electronic voucher to your guide at time of boarding </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Cameras and camcorders are welcome and encouraged! </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Comfortable clothing and shoes recommended </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Collapsible wheelchairs permitted with 48 hour advance notice </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Passengers must confirm Hotel AND select pickup time at least 48 hours prior to tour </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '20180821112900_192.jpg', '20180821112900_450.jpg', '', '236158', 5, 1, 46, 27, '2018-08-21 11:29:00'),
(31, 'Niagara Falls,Niagara Falls Boat Tours', '', 'Canada', 'Niagara-on-the-Lake Whirlpool Boat Tour â€“ Wet Jet Ride', 'niagara-on-the-lake-whirlpool-boat-tour-wet-jet-ride', '(An Exciting Ride Down the Niagara River Rapids)', 'Niagara-on-the-Lake Whirlpool Wet Jet Boat Ride | Niagara Falls Tour', ' ', 'A 45-minute open jet boat ride on the Niagara River and Niagara Rapids. Departure from Niagara-on-the-Lake. Get wet, feel the power of the rapids. Read booking details.', '<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n\r\n<p>This 45 minute Jet Boat adventure will take your on the ride of your life along the Niagara River into the Niagara Gorge and through the Devil\'s Hole Rapids.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Change of clothing is highly recommended.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can easily register online by selecting the Green \"Book This Tour\" button.&nbsp; All participants must sign a participation agreement and attend a mandatory safety orientation before departing on the tour.&nbsp;</p>\r\n     \r\n\r\n<table class=\"tbl_wet_jet\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n\r\n<tbody>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<th>Niagara-on-the-Lake Departure Times</th>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<th>April 28 â€“ May 18</th>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<th>May 19 â€“ June 22</th>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<th>June 23 â€“ Sept. 3</th>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<th>Sept. 4 â€“ Oct. 21</th>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<td><strong>Wet Jet Boat</strong><br>\r\nComplete change of<br>\r\nclothing needed</td>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">â€“</td>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">â€“</td>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">11:30AM<br>\r\n1:45PM<br>\r\n3:15PM<br>\r\n4:45PM</td>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">â€“</td>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</tbody>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Niagara Falls', '45 minutes', '0', '', '', 'CA', 'Price', 75.71, ' ', '', ' ', 0, ' ', ' ', 50.85, ' ', ' ', 0, ' ', '', '', '', '<ul class=\"inclu_list\">\r\n<li>Ponchos</li>\r\n<li>Water shoes</li>\r\n<li>Life jackets</li>\r\n<li>Free changing rooms</li>\r\n<li>Locker for valuables</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '                  <p>A full (100%) refund will be provided by Niagara Falls Tour for any cancellation request received at least 48 hours before the scheduled departure time. Any cancellation requested within 48 hours of the scheduled departure time will receive <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n                  ', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<strong>How can I stay Dry on this trip?</strong>\r\n<p>Take the Jet Dome tour where you do the same tour but in a covered boat instead of the open-top jet boat</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Can seniors take this trip?</strong>\r\n<p>There is no age limit, though there is a height limit (you must be at least 44 inches tall or 3 feet 4 inches). You must be of good health, free of heart, neck or back issues and not pregnant.</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<strong>How is seating arranged?</strong>\r\n<p>Seating is first come, first served and cannot be reserved. Young children (under 10 must sit towards the back of the boat)</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>How long is the trip?</strong>\r\n<p>Trips departing from Niagara-on-the-Lake are 60 minutes (round trip) while tours departing from Niagara Falls ON and Lewiston NY are 45 minutes (round trip). This time difference is because of the locations\' proximity to the Niagara Gorge. All 3 departures spend the same amount of time in the rapids!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does the boat go?</strong>\r\n<p>From either departure point, we travel upriver (south) and into the Niagara Gorge. Once in the gorge, 175 ft walls ascend from above the water line. The boat makes its way into the famous whirlpool and then we head back on down (north) through Devil\'s Hole Rapids. You return to the same location from which you boarded as our tour is a round trip excursion.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>How many people does the boat hold?</strong>\r\n<p>There are 8 boats in the fleet. The Jet Dome holds 40 passengers. The Wet Jet boats hold 48 passengers each and two hold 54 passengers.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h2 class=\"heading4\">Boats</h2>\r\n<div class=\"txt\">\r\n                  <p>8 Jet Boats. These boats use a triple turbo diesel water jet system for both propulsion and steering. They are custom built with passenger safety as the most important feature.</p>                  \r\n                  </div>\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Address (Departure Location)</h2>\r\n<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<p>Niagara-On-The-Lake Falls Departure Location<br>\r\n61 Melville St, Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON L0S 1J0</p>        \r\n                  </div>\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Printed Voucher</h2>\r\n<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<p>A Printed voucher of your booking confirmation should be presented to Whirlpool Jet Boat Tours staff upon arrival.</p>        \r\n                  </div>', '20180821113659_777.jpg', '20180821113659_658.jpg', '', 'asd', 5, 1, 18, 28, '2018-08-21 11:36:59'),
(32, 'Niagara Falls', 'Sightseeing tours', 'USA', 'Canadian Rainbow Tour Niagara Falls, Ontario (USA pickups only)', 'canadian-rainbow-tour-niagara-falls-ontario-usa-pickups-only-', 'Half Day Trip (4 Hours)', 'Rainbow Tour Niagara Falls Ontario (USA Pickups Only) | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Rainbow Tour Niagara Falls Ontario (USA Pickups Only) | Niagara Falls Tour', 'Day tour of Niagara Falls Ontario, 4 hours duration. See Niagara Falls from the Canadian side. See other attractions like the Floral Clock, Niagara Whirlpool.', '<h3 class=\"heading3\">Canadian Rainbow Bus Tour (Niagara Falls, NY Hotel pickups only)</h3>\r\n<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n<p>Daily Bus Tours from Niagara New York to Visit the Canadian Side of Niagara Falls</p>\r\n<div class=\"read-more\">\r\n<p>Bring your passport and spend a day on the Canadian Side of Niagara Falls!  </p>\r\n<p>This 4 hour tour will take you to all the popular attractions on the Canadian side of the Falls including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hornblower Boat Cruise</li>\r\n<li>Niagara Whirlpool</li>\r\n<li>Floral Clock</li>\r\n<li>Souvenir shopping at Table Rock</li>\r\n<li>Much more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Niagara Falls', '4 Hours', ' 0', '', '', 'US', 'Price', 109.95, ' ', '', ' ', 0, ' ', 'Children (5-12 years)', 74.95, ' ', 'Infants (0-4 years)', 0, ' Free', '', '', '', '<ul class=\"inclu_list\">\r\n<li>Hornblower Boat Cruise</li>\r\n<li>Escalation up the Skylon Tower for a bird\'s eye view of the Niagara Falls</li>\r\n<li>FREE return pass to go back and visit the Skylon Tower on your own</li>\r\n<li>Guided Tour of Niagara Falls, Ontario and surrounding region with full licensed guide/driver</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '<p>Complimentary Pickup from most downtown Niagara Falls USA hotels (you must contact the number provided on your ticket at least 24 hours before your tour and provide your pickup destination).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You must present a printed copy of your electronic voucher to your guide at time of boarding</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Border crossing documents such as Passport and/or Visa required for cross-border tours</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Departure Times:</h2>\r\n<p><strong>AMERICAN DEPARTURES:</strong> 11AM(TOUR START TIME)</p>\r\n<p><strong>BUFFALO DEPARTURES:</strong> 11AM(TOUR START TIME</p>', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<p>A full refund issued by ToNiagara if your tour is cancelled at <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">least 48 hours</span> before scheduled tour departure (this includes any issue arising at the U.S.A/Canada Border). <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NO REFUND</span> will be issued if the tour is cancelled less than <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">48 hours</span> before scheduled tour departure time.</p>\r\n</div>', '<strong>What type of documentation do I need for crossing the border on my tour?</strong>\r\n<p>United States and Canadian citizens ages 16 and older must present one of the following travel documents at the border:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n<li> Valid U.S. or Canadian Passport</li>\r\n<li> Enhanced Driver\'s License (EDL)</li>\r\n<li> U.S. Passport Card</li>\r\n<li> Trusted Traveler Program Card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"read-more2\">\r\n<p>United States and Canadian citizens under the age of 16, or under the age of 19 traveling with a school, religious or other youth group, must present one of the following travel documents at the border:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n<li> Original or certified copy of birth certificate</li>\r\n<li> Naturalization Certificate</li>\r\n<li> Consular report of birth abroad</li>\r\n<li> Canadian Citizenship Card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Lawful Permanent Residents of the United States must present a Permanent Resident Card (\"Green Card\", INS Form I-1551) at the border.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Residents of nations other than the United States and Canada may require a Canadian Visa along with their passport to enter Canada. Contact your national consulate before leaving home. International visitors will require passports to cross the border. Citizens of some countries may require a Canadian Visa as well. Be sure to check with our staff when booking your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the most up-to-date border crossing information, please access the following website: www.cbp.gov (Subject to Change)</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does my tour depart from?</strong>\r\n<p>There are multiple pickup points on both sides of the border, all within walking or driving distance from most hotels. We will provide directions to your departure point when you confirm  your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to wait until I arrive at Niagara Falls to book my tour?</strong>\r\n<p>Due to the popularity of our tours, we recommend that you reserve your seats as soon as possible to guard against the possibility of a sell-out.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>What type of clothing is recommended for the tour?</strong>\r\n<p>Comfortable walking shoes or sneakers are recommended. It is always a few degrees cooler near the water, so a jacket or sweater is also a good idea for cooler temperatures.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need to bring money on tour with me?</strong>\r\n<p>The price of your tour includes all attraction and parking fees. You may want to bring some spending money or a credit card with you as you will be given the opportunity to purchase snacks or souvenirs. Tipping your tour guide is at your discretion.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you pickup from Buffalo?</strong>\r\n<p>Yes, we pick-up from any downtown or airport hotel in Buffalo for our tours.  There is an additional $40 round trip fee per party for these pickups, you can discuss when you confirm your tour.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Are meals included?</strong>\r\n<p>No, meals are not provided.  Breaks will be given throughout the tour in order for guests to purchase something to eat on their own.</p>\r\n</div>', '<div class=\"m_txt\">\r\n<h2 class=\"heading4\">Other information</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"cencel\">\r\n<li>Tour itinerary is subject to change without notice</li>\r\n<li> Cameras and camcorders are welcome and encouraged!</li>\r\n<li> Comfortable clothing and shoes recommended</li>\r\n<li> Border crossing documents such as Passport and/or Visa required for cross-border tours</li>\r\n<li> Collapsable wheelchairs permitted with 24 hour advance notice</li>\r\n<li> MUST confirm 24-hours in advance</li>\r\n<li> No refunds will be made with less than 48 hour notice or the lack of border crossing documentation (if required for tour)</li>\r\n<li> Children 0-4 are FREE and considered lap children, thus NO seat will be reserved</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '20180821114331_825.jpg', '20180821114331_241.jpg', '', '236551', 5, 1, 34, 29, '2018-08-21 11:43:31');
